71	faq_exhibitor	<div><strong>How do I apply for an exhibition at the Online Home Education Expo?</strong></div><ul><li>Download the Application Form.</li><li>Fill in the PDF Application Form and email it to <a href="mailto:expo@tuisskolers.org">expo@tuisskolers.org</a>.</li><li>If your application is successful, we will email your invoice and login details to set up your stall. </li><li>For any enquiries or assistance contact us at <a href="mailto:expo@tuisskolers.org">expo@tuisskolers.org</a> or +27 87 231 1644. </li></ul><div><strong>When can I setup my stall?</strong></div><ul><li>As soon as we have sent you your exhibitor login details you can start setting up your stall.</li></ul><div><strong>What are the starting and ending times of the expo?</strong></div><ul><li>The expo will start at Tuesday 13 October 2020 at 09:00 and will end on Saturday 17 October at 24:00.</li></ul><div><strong>Is it compulsory to exhibit for the entire duration of the expo?</strong></div><ul><li>Although exhibitor monitoring of the stall for the complete duration of the expo is not required, we recommend that the exhibitor will be available from 8:00 to 17:00 on expo days to answer visitor enquiries. When you are not available, visitors will still be able to leave you a message. If you are available after hours, you can encourage visitor enquiries, by putting a notice on your stall.</li></ul><div><strong>What is the difference between a Webcam Interview and a Speaker Session?</strong></div><ul><li>Presentations at the expo will provide an online equivalent to speaker sessions in an auditorium at a physical event.</li><li>The Presentations page will contain three types of presentations:<ul><li><strong>Featured Presentations:</strong> Topical presentations by keynote speakers arranged by the organisers. </li><li><strong>Webcam Interviews:</strong> Bouwe van der Eems, from SA Homeschoolers, will do a recorded interview with you via Zoom or GoTo Meeting before the expo. Apart from it being available on the Presentations page you can will be able use it for marketing and to also display it as one of the video's in your stall.</li><li><strong>Speaker Session:</strong> This is a video-recorded speaker presentation of which the production is your responsibility. Although you may use this opportunity to promote your Products and Services, from experience on what people tend to listen to, we recommend a topical approach that has the benefit of confirming you or your company as an authority on the subject. In the description you can link back to the stall. You can also use this video as one of your videos at your stall. The suggested length for the video is not more than half an hour.</li></ul></li><li>All presentations will be viewable throughout the duration of the expo.  </li></ul><div><strong>How does the Exhibitor login work?</strong></div><ul><li>You will receive an email with your email address, password and the link to the website. </li></ul><div><strong>How does the Live Chat work?</strong></div><ul><li>The live chat will be a feature on your stall where the visitors can ask questions and you can answer immediately, or they can leave you a message if you can't attend immediately.</li></ul>	Event	1	2020-09-10 07:59:32.318678	2020-09-20 18:03:37.408013
