373	introduction	<div>Singapore Maths is the generic name of the Maths curriculum or syllabus that is created by the Education Ministry in Singapore for use in Singapore schools. As more and more people around the world became fascinated by the astounding success of Singapore students in mathematics, they began referring to Singapore's Maths curriculum as simply Singapore Maths.<br><br></div><div><strong>THE SINGAPORE MATHS CURRICULUM FRAMEWORK</strong></div><div><action-text-attachment content-type="image" url="https://singaporemaths.co.za/img/cms/Singapore%20Mathematics%20Curriculum%20Framework.png" width="499" height="327"></action-text-attachment></div>	Company	52	2020-09-29 15:17:55.962802	2020-10-12 14:47:07.108163
390	workshop_facilitator_info	<div>Facilitator <strong>Bouwe van der Eems</strong> and his wife Debbie have homeschooled their 5 children who have all finished their matric. Their children have chosen different matric options that suit their learning styles and were aligned with their career choices.<br><br><strong>Annerine Wenhold</strong> has been a home educator for more than 6 years, following a 19-year career in business optimization and environmental management in a corporate project management environment, whilst balancing a sporting (cycling) career. Apart from researching and educating her family, she participates in local co-ops, presents bible school, runs a successful coaching business, and is active in various community projects.<br><br><strong>Shirley Erwee</strong> is a homeschooling mother, who has been home educating her own 6 children plus two others for over 20 years, since 1997. In 2016, after years of recommending the GED® as a solution for homeschoolers and others needing to get a grade 12 equivalent, she launched Online GED Prep® South Africa to help candidates wishing to prepare for the GED® tests. Shirley is also a home education activist and consultant, as well as a curriculum provider offering various other learning materials for South African homeschoolers, including the <strong><em>Footprints On Our Land </em></strong>programs. In 2014 and 2015 she authored two books on homeschooling in South Africa, namely <strong><em>Homeschooling the Primary Years </em></strong>and <strong><em>Homeschooling High School </em></strong>and she offers two series of webinars for parents starting home education: S<em>tarting Homeschooling</em> and <em>Homeschooling High School</em>.<br><br>Tracey Howard and Sharon Genlloud are homeschool moms who run the Global Village College. They have lots of experience with the Cambridge curriculum. They are passionate educators who have homeschooled their own children.  With extensive expertise and experience in education and consulting, they guide students on their academic pathway to achieve success in work and life.<br><strong>Tracey Howard,</strong> our Director, is a mom who started homeschooling her own children in order to provide them with an education she believed would stretch and challenge them to reach their potential and would prepare them for the future.  Her combined expertise in organization development consultancy and education perfectly equips her to guide students on their academic pathway to find meaningful employment and to learn the skills they need for the 4th Industrial workplace.  She has a Masters degree and draws on extensive research and diverse experience in youth development, education, and school management to help young people on the exciting journey to acquire the skills and qualifications they will need to thrive in a rapidly changing and competitive global world.<br><br><strong>Sharon Genlloud</strong>, our Head of Educational Studies, is also a mom who has walked the path of homeschooling her son who has dyslexia. As a qualified teacher with an Honours degree in Education, she found that the traditional school system was unable to successfully accommodate her own child's education.  Based on her experience and after exploring all the options available to South African students, she chose Cambridge as her curriculum of choice.  The methodical delivery of curricula, the incredible resources available, and the flexibility of the examination series ensure that your child is given the best opportunities to achieve an internationally recognized matric qualification right here in South Africa. Her experience over the last 16 years as Head of Department, Deputy Principal, and Principal has contributed greatly to the knowledge and guidance she can offer our students.</div>	Workshop	9	2020-09-30 13:49:01.805374	2020-11-02 12:50:13.878203
