274	about_exhibitor	<div><br></div><h1><strong>Brief Background</strong></h1><div><br>In the design of Love2Learn, we researched curricula from America, Canada, the UK, Australia and the national curriculum of South Africa; and from there we compiled the scope and sequence of Love2Learn. <br><br>We are humbled in being able to share with you that today, Love2Learn is being used across the breadth of education; from learning centres and independent schools in 3 different countries, right through to families homeschooling one or more children in more than 25 countries around the world. <br><br><br></div><h1><strong>Our Statement of Faith</strong></h1><div><strong>(And the History Behind the Love2Learn Logo Designs)<br></strong><br></div><div><br></div><div>Dear fellow and prospective Home-Educator… Welcome to Love2Learn Curriculum!<br><br></div><div>Love2Learn Curriculum stands on the triune doctrinal foundation of:</div><ol><li><strong>The unique authority of the Word of God the Father.</strong> We believe that the Bible is the only written revelation of and from God and that it is therefore all we need for faith and life.</li><li><strong>The Lordship and centrality of Jesus Christ.</strong> We believe that Jesus Christ is God the Son and the full revelation of the Godhead to mankind. He is head of the church and Lord of our lives. As a result, we are to base our doctrine and practice on what He said and did.</li><li><strong>The ministry of the Holy Spirit.</strong> We believe that we are to trust and obey God the Holy Spirit and that we are to embrace all that the Scriptures reveal of Him and His ministry.</li></ol><div><br></div><div><strong><em>The world still has a way to go before homeschooling is openly embraced and recognised as the better option for the education of our children and ultimately for preparing them for life!<br></em></strong><br></div><div>We have watched with growing excitement and an unequivocal acknowledgement of God’s grace and provision how homeschooling has mushroomed since we first started homeschooling our own two daughters in early 2000, both internationally and more-so in South Africa. It has been so encouraging to see the trend in society gravitate from an initial antagonistic suspicion, to intrigue and in more recent years, tentative acceptance and at times even admiration!<br><br></div><div>We have been privileged over the years, via numerous television and radio interviews as well as seminars and presentations, to share our passion for homeschooling and Love2Learn Curriculum with families; and we are both delighted and humbled that today Love2Learn is used by independent learning centres and cottage schools in three countries and homeschooling families in more than 25 countries, across the globe!<br><br></div><div>It is with great joy and an acknowledgement of God’s abundant grace, guidance and patience that we take this opportunity to introduce you to Love2Learn Curriculum and our commitment to Bring Life to Learning!<br><br></div><div><strong>Our prayer is that you too will embrace homeschooling as the marvelous catalyst that God has given each one of us as parents, for restoring families and impacting generations – ultimately producing God-honouring, vibrant and effective members of society, in our precious children!<br></strong><br></div><div>We would love to have the pleasure and privilege of walking alongside you on this journey.<br><br></div><div>May God in His unmerited grace, grant you wisdom and discernment in making this wonderful, life-changing move.<br><br></div><div><strong>Yours in homeschooling!<br></strong><br></div><div><strong>Marc Ries and the Love2Learn Team<br><br></strong><br></div><div><br><br></div><h1><strong>The History Behind the Love2Learn Logo Designs</strong></h1><div><br></div><div><action-text-attachment content-type="image" url="https://love2learn.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/BL2L-Color-Logo-Medium.png" width="802" height="160" caption="The Love2Learn Logo"></action-text-attachment></div><div>We were very deliberate in both our colour choice and design.<br><br></div><ul><li>The <strong>“Crown”</strong> is an unequivocal acknowledgement of the fact that we seek to honour and serve the Lord Jesus Christ as our King! <em>“As for me and my household, we will serve the Lord” </em><strong>Joshua 24:15</strong><em>.</em></li><li>The use of gold in our logo is highly significant for two reasons: Gold is considered to be both precious and valuable – much like our children, only they are much, much more so!</li><li>The numeral <strong>“2”</strong> (as opposed to the letters “to” or “two”) reminds us of our united efforts to honour the Lord, in that He is with us, guiding and ordering our (Love2Learn’s) efforts to supply curriculum to you; and, at the same time, He is with you in your efforts, as you seek to disciple your children through homeschooling. As Paul says, we are co-workers with God (<strong>1 Corinthians 3:9</strong>) – how awesome is that!</li><li>We carried the gold colour from the “Crown” through to the “2”, as a depiction and reminder of the fact that we are not homeschooling on our own. God, in the person and power of His Holy Spirit, is always with us, strengthening, guiding, comforting and undertaking for us as we walk this journey – <em>Be strong and courageous. Do not be afraid or terrified because of them, for the Lord your God goes with you; He will never leave you nor forsake you.”</em> <strong>Deuteronomy 31:6</strong></li><li>“Bring Life to Learning” too has a double-meaning…<br> 1. The beautiful, full-colour and photo-rich books and resources that permeate throughout Love2Learn, ensure that a child experience a “living” education. The books make the child want to turn the page; they capture the imagination, captivate and escalate a child to new planes and levels of thinking.<br> 2. More importantly, the very best way to Bring <strong>LIFE</strong> to Learning in a child’s education, is to teach them to get to know Jesus – who is Life, serve Him and become more like Him; and help others to do the same.</li></ul><div><em>“I am the way and the truth and the life. No one comes to the Father except through me.”</em> <strong>John 14:6</strong></div><div><br></div><div><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSI-Z2lkOi8vZXZlbnRzLXBsYXRmb3JtL0FjdGl2ZVN0b3JhZ2U6OkJsb2IvMjkxMz9leHBpcmVzX2luBjsAVEkiDHB1cnBvc2UGOwBUSSIPYXR0YWNoYWJsZQY7AFRJIg9leHBpcmVzX2F0BjsAVDA=--922b0bfb68dec4b462dbf54ae4442d253ad104ec" content-type="image/jpeg" url="http://homeschoolexpo.africa/files/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBbUVMIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--3b497ed572aacd9a6a5465b8d3be9e91f18ef937/L2L%20Icon%20(Smaller).JPG" filename="L2L Icon (Smaller).JPG" filesize="10929" width="163" height="141" previewable="true" presentation="gallery" caption="Love2Learn Icon"></action-text-attachment></div><div>With the <strong>“L2L”</strong> “icon” logo, we have tried to give further emphasis to this by placing the crown above, so that it clearly depicts (and acknowledges) God's covering over all of us.<br><br></div><div><br></div><div><em>To Him who is able to keep you from stumbling and to present you before His glorious presence without fault and with great joy— to the only God our Saviour be glory, majesty, power and authority, through Jesus Christ our Lord, before all ages, now and forevermore! Amen.</em><strong> ~Jude 1:24-25</strong></div><div><br></div>	Company	40	2020-09-23 14:58:21.739252	2020-10-12 20:56:01.934054
158	about_exhibitor	<div><a href="http://www.south-african-homeschool-curriculum.com/south-african-homeschool-curriculum.html">Footprints on Our Land</a> was made by homeschoolers for homeschoolers. The authors, Shirley Erwee and Wendy Young have both been homeschooling for over 20 years. We are both respected as veteran homeschooling experts. We are avid readers and love researching parenting and homeschooling and we bring you our <strong>collective passion </strong>and<strong> expertise</strong> in these areas.<br><br>Since we first launched our South African homeschool curriculum series in 2003, we have served thousands of families and earned a reputation as a favourite supplier of <strong>uniquely South African</strong> resources. We also have expatriate South African families in over 15 countries abroad using our various products.<br> More and more home schooling families are enjoying a family-oriented rather than classroom style of homeschooling that enables them to study South Africa’s rich heritage and raise up children that desire to make a difference in their country’s future. <br><br>Our gallery of photos shows many of our clients enjoying their unique South African learning experiences.<br><br></div><h1><strong>Our story</strong></h1><div><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSI9Z2lkOi8vZXZlbnRzLXBsYXRmb3JtL0FjdGl2ZVN0b3JhZ2U6OkJsb2IvODI3P2V4cGlyZXNfaW4GOwBUSSIMcHVycG9zZQY7AFRJIg9hdHRhY2hhYmxlBjsAVEkiD2V4cGlyZXNfYXQGOwBUMA==--f5b16876e8a8daddea32a0b520278c9fb1f75b13" content-type="image/jpeg" url="http://homeschoolexpo.africa/files/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBanNEIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--abd845b553830db208b6bf96cecb7e4372212fa4/erwee%20family.jpg" filename="erwee family.jpg" filesize="76993" width="1280" height="680" previewable="true" presentation="gallery" caption="Erwee family"></action-text-attachment> </div><div><br></div><div>In 2002, we both realised that we were on the hunt for South African historical literature to give our children a Charlotte Mason style education using "living books".  We teamed up and began to create Footprints on Our Land. Every night we would tuck our children up with a book and a prayer and then head to our computers to research until late, searching for authors in South Africa and elsewhere that made history come alive. We would then read and read and read to find just the right books and once we had found quality stories, we would create lesson plans, drawing out themes and ideas from within the book covers. And all of this on a dial-up connection!<br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSI9Z2lkOi8vZXZlbnRzLXBsYXRmb3JtL0FjdGl2ZVN0b3JhZ2U6OkJsb2IvNDk2P2V4cGlyZXNfaW4GOwBUSSIMcHVycG9zZQY7AFRJIg9hdHRhY2hhYmxlBjsAVEkiD2V4cGlyZXNfYXQGOwBUMA==--84b085f9ddc51b804015ab9fba6b511d2f02772c" content-type="image/jpeg" url="http://homeschoolexpo.africa/files/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBdkFCIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--126ea92f013b49243f2a929db8704e5348c83b9d/SS_Youngs_Family_Shoot_19-2.jpg" filename="SS_Youngs_Family_Shoot_19-2.jpg" filesize="11612128" width="4800" height="3200" previewable="true" presentation="gallery" caption="Young Family"></action-text-attachment><br><br></div><div>We knew that other homeschooling parents, like us, needed a programme that would delight and inspire their children, but make homeschooling easier and stress-free for the adult. You don't need a curriculum that drives you like a slave master and adds stress to your busy days! <br><br><em>Footprints on Our Land - South Africa's Heritage</em>,  for ages 7-12, was our first creation. As both of us had preschool children, we then produced <em>Little Footprints</em> for ages 4-8 years, which uses picture story books to teach younger children about our land, people, plants and animals as well as art and craft and pre-maths and reading skills.<br><br></div><div>Two years later, to cater for older children, aged 12-16 years, we launched <em>Footprints into the 21st Century</em>, which covers the last 100 years of South African history, natural science, language skills, life skills and Christian living, also using living books. <br><br>Our 2020 project is the creating of a HOMEgrown Afrikaans literature-based South African programme, due for launch in December - <em>Voetspore</em>.<br><br></div><div>Our programmes have delighted thousands of homeschooling families over the years and as we are first, homeschooling moms and secondly, curriculum providers. We understand all aspects of home education. Parents know they are safe with us – we’ve been in the trenches and received our stripes. Don't miss out on a favourite South Africa homeschool experience.<br><br>“<em>We are thoroughly enjoying it. It makes you love and appreciate South Africa. It makes you want to go and explore your own backyard and your city/town to try and find our local treasures. You can also chop and change and make it your own as much as you want to. I as a parent might even be enjoying it more than my kids!”</em> ~ Bronwyn Murray<br><br></div><div><em>“As an adult studying our history through Footprints, I’ve been struck by how strongly I feel emotionally about some of the literature! During my childhood and teen years we were fed such terrible propoganda. It has been a delight to read of other’s perspectives and experiences through the wonderful collection of literature, and I find a renewed understanding of our history.”</em> ~ Nadene Esterhuizen</div><div><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSI-Z2lkOi8vZXZlbnRzLXBsYXRmb3JtL0FjdGl2ZVN0b3JhZ2U6OkJsb2IvMTE5OD9leHBpcmVzX2luBjsAVEkiDHB1cnBvc2UGOwBUSSIPYXR0YWNoYWJsZQY7AFRJIg9leHBpcmVzX2F0BjsAVDA=--1a8d8b997d30bc8d31947f25e08a40dae0f13254" content-type="image/png" url="http://homeschoolexpo.africa/files/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBcTRFIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--e06de6d020082e37fca74a5c7c153fddb3afd65f/Little%20Footprints%204-8%20year%20olds%20South%20Africa%20in%20picture%20story%20books.png" filename="Little Footprints 4-8 year olds South Africa in picture story books.png" filesize="1231888" width="2050" height="780" previewable="true" presentation="gallery" caption="Our four uniquely HOMEgrown South African homeschooling programs"></action-text-attachment><br><br></div><div><a href="http://www.south-african-homeschool-curriculum.com/child-literature-lesson-plans.html"><strong>Little Footprints</strong></a> can be used for children in the age range of 4-8yrs. This programme  will delight your family with picture story books set in South African urban and rural spaces, from desert to seashore. You and your children will learn about our diverse culture groups, our amazing plant and animal life as well as enjoy lessons in Bible character, geography, science, art and crafts and school readiness skills. Little Footprints can be used with your young children and generally takes between 12-18 months to work through. </div><div><br></div><div><a href="http://www.south-african-homeschool-curriculum.com/literature-based-curriculum.html"><strong>Footprints on Our Land</strong></a> is our famous, best-selling literature-based curriculum centered around South African historical fiction. This programme is aimed at children between the ages of 7 and 14. It is a multi-level unit study beginning in 1488 when the Khoi-San first encountered Bartholomew Dias on his travels around the Cape and it ends in the early 1900s just after the South African War. But it is not only a history curriculum! Being a unit study, the lesson plans are built around the children’s literature which means you and your children will do lessons in geography, biology and nature study, science, language arts, cooking, art, crafts, technology and bible study. This program can be used comfortably with many children for 2 years.</div><div><br></div><div><a href="http://www.south-african-homeschool-curriculum.com/high-school-homeschool-curriculum.html"><strong>Footprints into the 21st Century</strong></a> is an original and uniquely South African high school homeschool unit study curriculum which presents teens with some of the best books that portray this era in the history of our country. It includes historical fiction, poetry, reference books as well as biographies of people who contributed to the events of the century. It has recently been updated to include the pain of the Angolan Bush War, the Woman’s March to Pretoria, the ever changing South African faces in politics, the drama of the State Capture Report, along with the history that we know – or thought we knew – of the Apartheid Era and the Freedom Struggle and more.</div><div>In this one-year program for 12 – 16 year olds,  you will  journey through the last 110+ years of South African history. You will look at the major biomes of South African from bush veld to mangrove swamp. You and your children will be challenged to do hard things and to think deeply about the twists and turns that post-modern thinking has taken. Your teens will be encouraged to look at 21st Century world living in the age of social media. They will do an in depth study of South African’s voting and political system. And more!</div><div><br></div><div>Our Footprints programmes will allow you to relax and really <strong>enjoy your homeschooling experience</strong> without trying to follow the teacher + text book + classroom model, with all its limitations! Our South African homeschool curriculum programmes are created to SAVE YOU TIME and ENERGY, simplify your life, build your confidence and minimize the stress associated with educating your children at home…it’s truly an opportunity to give your children a living education!</div><div><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSI9Z2lkOi8vZXZlbnRzLXBsYXRmb3JtL0FjdGl2ZVN0b3JhZ2U6OkJsb2IvNDcyP2V4cGlyZXNfaW4GOwBUSSIMcHVycG9zZQY7AFRJIg9hdHRhY2hhYmxlBjsAVEkiD2V4cGlyZXNfYXQGOwBUMA==--63f257fbe1dc7643e65087a52eb127b2025d434d" content-type="image/png" url="http://homeschoolexpo.africa/files/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBdGdCIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--b50f866f36d15008fd542eecd7b80fa0a1a0bed4/Little%20Footprints%204-8%20year%20olds%20South%20Africa%20in%20picture%20story%20books.png" filename="Little Footprints 4-8 year olds South Africa in picture story books.png" filesize="42246" width="2050" height="780" previewable="true" presentation="gallery" caption="."></action-text-attachment><br>Voetspore has been birthed out of the ongoing requests of Afrikaans homeschooling parents to have access to a Charlotte Mason styled education using resources from South Africa, living books and life experience. Over the years of going to home education expos we have seen how limited the options are for Afrikaans families who long to give their children a living education like Footprints offers, but to do this in their mother tongue.</div><div> </div><div>The task was not an easy one, based on our own first language being English, needing to source the books – and read them – but it has resulted in the program you find in the following pages. While it does not replicate the original Footprints format, Afrikaans families now have a chronological literature-based home education program from the early 14th century through to modern day South Africa.  <action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSI9Z2lkOi8vZXZlbnRzLXBsYXRmb3JtL0FjdGl2ZVN0b3JhZ2U6OkJsb2IvNDczP2V4cGlyZXNfaW4GOwBUSSIMcHVycG9zZQY7AFRJIg9hdHRhY2hhYmxlBjsAVEkiD2V4cGlyZXNfYXQGOwBUMA==--a86dd7f1b910b89472fa4cede51ea56f4ab96609" content-type="image/png" url="http://homeschoolexpo.africa/files/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBdGtCIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--8a7decd983df1cd471262290148d90f8efbeda3d/Voetspore%20Mock%20Up.png" filename="Voetspore Mock Up.png" filesize="2473355" width="2000" height="1300" previewable="true" presentation="gallery" caption="Voetspore - via Afrikaanse Families"></action-text-attachment></div><div> </div>	Company	14	2020-09-15 11:49:23.739471	2020-10-13 06:20:31.111751
