273	products_and_services	<div><br></div><h1><strong>How Love2Learn Works In A Nutshell</strong></h1><div><br><strong>Love2Learn Curriculum comprises a combination of two categories of subjects, BOTH of which are required in order to ensure a comprehensive education for a child:</strong></div><div> </div><ol><li><strong>Discipline Studies</strong></li><li><strong>Content Studies</strong></li></ol><ul><li>For more information in this regard, please visit <a href="https://love2learn.co.za/how-our-curriculum-fits-together/"><strong>How Our Curriculum Fits Together</strong></a>.</li><li>For very comprehensive guidance based on the number of your children you have and their respective grade levels, please visit <a href="https://love2learn.co.za/how-to-choose-your-subjects/"><strong>How To Choose Your Subjects</strong></a>.</li></ul><div><strong><em>Please be advised that Love2Learn is MODULAR in its design. Consequently you are NOT required to order the full range of subjects we offer in our Disciplined Studies and Content Studies. You are welcome to “cherry-pick” subjects to tailor-make a curriculum for each child.               </em></strong></div><div><br><br></div><h1><strong>Our Alignment with a Child’s Developmental Progression:</strong></h1><div>For  an Overview of our Curriculum which includes our focus aligned with a Child’s Developmental Progression – click <a href="https://love2learn.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/LOVE2LEARN-CURRICULUM-OVERVIEW-Aug19.pdf"><strong><em>here</em></strong></a><em>.</em></div><div><br><br></div><h1><strong>PR1ME Mathematics - </strong><strong><em>The World’s Best Practice</em></strong><strong>:</strong></h1><div>Love2Learn is delighted to be able to offer families and Learning Centres, PR1ME Mathematics - a world-class programme based on the effective teaching and learning practices of Singapore, Republic of Korea and Hong Kong – all three of whom are consistent top performers in international studies.</div><div><br>The content in PR1ME Mathematics covers the five strands of mathematics across six grades/year levels: Numbers and Operations, Measurement, Geometry, Data Analysis and Algebra. PR1ME Mathematics teaches via <a href="https://emea.scholastic.com/en/scholastic-prime-mathematics/teaching-via-problem-solving">Problem Solving</a>, <a href="https://emea.scholastic.com/en/scholastic-prime-mathematics/metacognition-development">Develops Metacognition and Mathematical Thinking</a>, <a href="https://emea.scholastic.com/en/scholastic-prime-mathematics/effective-measurable-diagnostic">Is Effective, Measurable and Diagnostic</a>, <a href="https://emea.scholastic.com/en/scholastic-prime-mathematics/professional-learning-in-curriculum-framework">Incorporates Professional Learning Into the Curriculum Framework</a> and <a href="https://emea.scholastic.com/en/scholastic-prime-mathematics/innovative-instructional-content-via-technology">Uses Technology to Deliver Innovative Instructional Content</a>.</div><ul><li>Click this link to view by <a href="https://emea.scholastic.com/en/scholastic-prime-mathematics/table-of-contents#by-grades">Grade Levels</a>.</li><li>For more information, please see this <a href="https://emea.scholastic.com/en/scholastic-prime-mathematics/chapter-walkthrough">Chapter Walkthrough</a>.</li><li>Click this link for <a href="https://emea.scholastic.com/en/scholastic-prime-mathematics/sample-pages#grade-1">Sample Pages of Grade 1 – 6</a>; and then click on “<strong>Download all sample pages</strong>” button. </li><li>Please note that PR1ME Maths is offered from Grade 00 – Grade 6.</li></ul><div>For Grades 7 - 9, Love2Learn offers the Cambridge Secondary 1 and Checkpoint Mathematics, which act as ideal stepping stone preparation for the start of Int. GCSE in Grade 10.<br><br><br></div><h1><strong>Love2Learn’s English Curriculum – Literacy At Its VERY Best!</strong></h1><div>GRADES 1 – 6 follow a Skills Focus Pathway <br>GRADES 7 – 9 follow an Integrated Skills Pathway<strong><br></strong><a href="https://love2learn.co.za/2020/09/20/love2learns-new-english-curriculum-literacy-at-its-very-best/"><strong>Read more...</strong></a><br><br><br></div><h1><strong>Testing and Exams</strong></h1><ul><li>There are no official tests and exams in <strong>Love2Learn</strong> up to and including Grade 9. </li><li>Our method of assessment is quite different to mainstream schooling and arguably far better.</li><li>For more on this, please visit <a href="https://love2learn.co.za/">https://love2learn.co.za/</a> and scroll down till you come to FAQ; and then read up under “Testing and Exams”.</li></ul><div><br></div><h1><strong>What About Socialisation? </strong></h1><div>Please follow this <a href="https://love2learn.co.za/2020/04/14/homeschooling-but-what-about-socialisation/">link</a> to our Blog post in this regard.</div><div><br><br></div><h1><strong>Returning to Mainstream</strong></h1><div>In terms of re-entering mainstream, there are essentially the following options:</div><ul><li>You as the educator, compile a Report using the Template we supply to you; and present it to the school.</li><li>You have your child assessed by an independent assessor or Educational psychologist and present that official Report to the school.</li><li>Many schools (and growing) these days offer an “entrance exam”, which your child could write and gain eligibility if they pass.</li><li>My personal favourite would be that you take the portfolio of work completed in the past year of h-s and present that to the HOD or other Grade teacher. If you have been h-s with diligence, commitment and regularity, it is my firm belief that you will generate a portfolio of work that supersedes ANY school on the face of planet earth; and any competent teacher will be able to see that your child is comfortably on par with the students in that same grade in their school.</li></ul>	Company	40	2020-09-23 14:58:21.736309	2020-10-12 20:56:01.696108
