272	introduction	<div><br></div><h1><strong>A Very Warm Welcome!</strong></h1><div><br>Thank you for visiting us and for your valued interest in Love2Learn Curriculum material for your family.</div><div><br>As you do your research, you'll find that there are the following main options when it comes to homeschooling:</div><ol><li><strong>HOME-Schooling</strong>: These parents want to put the "HOME" back into schooling, but still maintain a high standard.</li><li><strong>SCHOOL-at-home</strong>: These are the parents that choose a curriculum that is normally CAPS-based and end up offering essentially an importation of the classroom into their homes. The curriculum  generally requires the relentless completion of worksheet after worksheet... and children thus end up doing what's commonly referred to as "school at home"!</li><li><strong>Eclectic schooling</strong>: These parents are somewhat more deliberate in the topics and/or goals that they have in mind, but they "cherry-pick" bits and pieces of resources and material from any number of sources in order to cover and meet these goals.</li><li><strong>Unschooling</strong>: These parents choose not to follow any kind of guideline/curriculum. In the main, they prefer to do their own thing, often simply pandering to the moods, whims and desires of their children.</li></ol><div><br>One of the many attractions of <strong>Love2Learn Curriculum</strong> is that, although we predominantly play in the No.1 arena, we are able to confidently serve families in all of the other three camps too. The reasons we can say this are because:</div><ol><li><strong>FLEXIBILITY</strong>: We offer parents the chance of being able to access a flexible curriculum with books, games, charts, etc., combined with enrichment subjects like Critical Thinking, STEM, Latin and the like. All the while, they can take comfort in the knowledge that the scope and sequence of each and every subject is thorough and comprehensively covered.</li><li><strong>ENGINE ROOMS</strong>: Our subjects in the main are supplied standard with Engine Rooms (daily guidance and lesson plans spanning 36 weeks), that take the headache out of lesson preparation, whilst affording parents and educators the chance for their God-given creativity, combined with the unique knowledge and understanding of their children, to come to the fore.</li><li><strong>TAILORED EDUCATION</strong>: Love2Learn is modular. We do not dictate minimum purchases beyond one subject at a time. The beauty of this is that it allows a parent/educator to tailor-make an offering to meet the needs of their unique child.</li></ol><div><br></div><div>What is so important to grasp, is that the HOME-schooling environment that we create with Love2Learn Curriculum is not one that creates pressure, nor is it a relentless completion of worksheets as you may recall from your schooling experience. Rather, we seek to engender a life-long love of learning via the inclusion of beautiful, full-colour, photo-rich, “living” books and the incorporation of hands-on activities as well as internet links, so that visual, auditory and kinaesthetic learning styles are accommodated in a fun way! The incorporation of material and activities that caters for Visual (“See it…”), Auditory (“Hear it…”) and Kinaesthetic (“Do it…”) learning preferences means that your child is able to cover the material in the “language” that they “speak”. </div><div><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSI-Z2lkOi8vZXZlbnRzLXBsYXRmb3JtL0FjdGl2ZVN0b3JhZ2U6OkJsb2IvMjU3OD9leHBpcmVzX2luBjsAVEkiDHB1cnBvc2UGOwBUSSIPYXR0YWNoYWJsZQY7AFRJIg9leHBpcmVzX2F0BjsAVDA=--93833e25fa0005b0f56bef820915b15e5b1b1135" content-type="image/jpeg" url="http://homeschoolexpo.africa/files/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBaElLIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--bf1af0752b6ee40a139a407f913d9999b6f23661/Learning%20Styles.JPG" filename="Learning Styles.JPG" filesize="20279" width="402" height="299" previewable="true" presentation="gallery" caption='There are 3 dominant Learning Styles - at L2L we call them "Learning Languages"'></action-text-attachment><br><br>We like to say that we <strong>Bring Life2Learning</strong>, whilst maintaining a high academic standard!<br><br></div><div>We are humbled that today <strong>Love2Learn Curriculum</strong> is being used across the breadth of education; from learning centres and independent schools in 3 different countries, right through to families homeschooling one or more children in more than 25 countries around the world!</div><div><br></div><div>Our experience of more than 20 years in homeschooling - both as a homeschooling family and as author and provider of Love2Learn Curriculum - has shown us that parents come to homeschooling for a variety of reasons... these can be Spiritual, better educational standards, safety, life-style and so on and so forth; and in far and away the majority of cases, they realise when they are in it, that it should have been their first choice! </div><div><br></div><ul><li>Please be sure to visit and read <a href="https://love2learn.co.za/the-unique-values-we-bring/"><strong>The Unique Value We Bring To Education</strong></a>.</li></ul><div><br>In the design phase of Love2Learn Curriculum, we researched curricula from USA, Canada, UK, Australia and the National Curriculum of SA; and from there compiled the scope and sequence of L2L from Gr00 – Gr9. </div><div><br></div><div>From Grade 10 to Grade 12 we offer preparation for the prestigious International GCSE (Grade 10/11 combined) and AS-Level (Gr12) examinations. The latter is recognised by every public University in South Africa, as well as by many other institutions around the world. In addition, we have included a spread of Cambridge Checkpoint and Cambridge Secondary 1 resources across our Grade 7, 8 and 9 subject offering, so that these levels create even more enhanced stepping-stones of preparation for the start of International GCSE in Grade 10.<br><br></div><div>For detailed information in this regard please visit <a href="http://www.iic-online.com/"><strong>Imperial International College</strong></a> (our sister company), who align with the Cambridge syllabus and offer online support for International GCSE and AS-Levels.</div><div><br></div><div><strong>In closing I would also encourage you to:</strong></div><div>       <strong>i.</strong>          Read through - and feel free to share it with others: <a href="http://www.nheri.org/research/research-facts-on-homeschooling.html"><strong>Research Facts on Homeschooling</strong></a><strong>.</strong></div><div>      <strong>ii.</strong>          If you’ve not already done so, <strong>DOWNLOAD OUR</strong> <strong>FREE PDF</strong> <a href="https://love2learn.co.za/homeschooling-a-better-education-for-a-better-future/"><strong>Homeschooling Handbook</strong></a>.</div><div><br></div><div><strong>We would love the chance to be of service to you and your family in your homeschooling journey - please let us know if we can assist you further.</strong></div><div><br></div><div>Book a <a href="https://love2learn.co.za/book-appointment/"><strong>FREE Telephonic/Google Meet/Skype/Zoom consultation</strong></a>.</div><div><br></div><div>My prayer is that God will Bless and guide you as you seek His will for your precious family.</div><div><br></div><div><strong>Marc Ries</strong></div><div>Managing Director</div>	Company	40	2020-09-23 14:58:21.732548	2020-10-12 20:56:01.457951
