32	products_and_services	<div><strong>Grades starting in 2021</strong><br>Foundation Phase (Grade R-3)<br>Intermediate Phase (Grade 4-6) <br>Senior Phase (Grade 7- 9)<br>FET (Grade 10-12) - <em>Will be phased in from 2021</em><br><br></div><div><strong>Our tailored approach makes us different</strong></div><div>Gone are the days where a child’s self-worth and accomplishments are measured against artificial conventions. By not feeling rushed to keep up with the rest of the class, and not feeling bored or held back when they are keen to move faster, we give your child the chance to claim their ground through their own achievements and reduce the anxiety associated with the usual one-size-fits-all model of schooling.<br><br><strong>Evolve </strong>is designed to take each child on a journey of personal mastery, using trend setting curriculum mapping systems developed by MIT, where they progress at their own deliberate or accelerated pace.<br><br></div><div><strong>Join us in helping your child to thrive in today’s world.</strong></div><ul><li><strong>Project-based</strong> learning with <strong>performance-based</strong> assessments</li><li><strong>Live online</strong> classes, <strong>mapped progress</strong> and <strong>reporting</strong></li><li><strong>Social interaction</strong> and <strong>peer collaboration</strong></li><li>Monthly <strong>adventure boxes </strong>(Grades R – 3)</li><li>Age-appropriate <strong>life coaching</strong></li><li>Affordable</li></ul><div><br><strong>At Evolve Online School, we follow  a careful balance of Synchronous and Asynchronous learning.</strong></div><div><strong> </strong></div><div><strong>Students learn together and collaborate in real time - Synchronous</strong></div><div>Learning is a deeply social activity and children need moments of meaningful connection. They will use Synchronous sessions to build a relationship with their Learning Activators. In the Foundation Phase we practice ‘looping’. This means that the same activators will stay with your child for more than one year to facilitate a deeper relationship and understanding of their unique needs. Much of the Synchronous time will be spent in discussions and collaborative learning with peers. We will be teaching our students how to collaborate before we expect them to do so. Students will attend scheduled group sessions and, at times, will schedule their own to complete the tasks.</div><div><strong> </strong></div><div><strong> </strong></div><div><strong>Students learn on their own, at their own pace and at a beneficial time - Asynchronous</strong></div><div>In a traditional classroom, a teacher does not have the tools to focus on the progress of each student before they must move on to the next topic. Children struggle due to gaps from previous years then fall further behind and become frustrated. Often, children are not challenged by the work and become bored. Both problems lead children to disengage from their learning and lose interest in the topic. </div><div> </div><div>The Asynchronous <strong>Evolve Online</strong> approach follows the individual progress of each child. Students move forward only when they are ready to do so, and once they have mastered each Item. They can also take a step back and address specific gaps without feeling rushed or self-conscious. The phased structure of this approach also allows students who excel in any specific subject to advance to work that challenges them, without having to wait for the whole class to catch up. The ability to progress faster if they are eager keeps learners engaged </div><div><br><strong>Empowering students through Digital Mastery</strong></div><div>Digital Mastery is a core leaning area from Grade R to 12. Your child’s future career may be found where none existed twenty years ago. Essential to their success is not only being familiar with the use of different technology but being able to create content for it. Our coding curriculum starts in Grade R. Evolve students also learn to become digitally-savvy, keep themselves safe online and able to distinguish between fake and fact</div><div><br></div><div><action-text-attachment content-type="image" url="https://lirp-cdn.multiscreensite.com/112c41b2/dms3rep/multi/opt/Digital+mastery-circular+element-480w.png" width="480" height="715"></action-text-attachment><br><action-text-attachment content-type="image" url="https://lirp-cdn.multiscreensite.com/112c41b2/dms3rep/multi/opt/ADvTECH%2BEvolve%2BOnline%2BSchool%2BFees%2B2021%2Bimage-1920w-960w.jpg" width="960" height="1024"></action-text-attachment><br><br></div>	Company	8	2020-09-09 09:20:00.08896	2020-09-30 12:43:09.697396
