 diverse culture groups, our amazing plant and animal life, as well as do lessons in Bible characters, geography, science, art and crafts and school readiness skills. Little Footprints generally takes between 12-18 months to complete. Be sure to watch our video on the video tab about this program and the gentle way of learning we offer.<br><br>“<em>Children are made readers in the laps of their parents.</em>“  ~ Emily Buchwald<br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSI9Z2lkOi8vZXZlbnRzLXBsYXRmb3JtL0FjdGl2ZVN0b3JhZ2U6OkJsb2IvNDY4P2V4cGlyZXNfaW4GOwBUSSIMcHVycG9zZQY7AFRJIg9hdHRhY2hhYmxlBjsAVEkiD2V4cGlyZXNfYXQGOwBUMA==--c563833aa90c3b1d95b834658bedf4869b9b7ae4" content-type="image/png" url="http://homeschoolexpo.africa/files/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBdFFCIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--f722075cf5c3922bb4ad59f9712984001cc3a1bc/2.png" filename="2.png" filesize="53081" width="2050" height="780" previewable="true" presentation="gallery" caption="."></action-text-attachment></div><div> <action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSI9Z2lkOi8vZXZlbnRzLXBsYXRmb3JtL0FjdGl2ZVN0b3JhZ2U6OkJsb2IvNDY1P2V4cGlyZXNfaW4GOwBUSSIMcHVycG9zZQY7AFRJIg9hdHRhY2hhYmxlBjsAVEkiD2V4cGlyZXNfYXQGOwBUMA==--6f48676590bc6d28f5fc23152f5dd8deaeea9c52" content-type="image/png" url="http://homeschoolexpo.africa/files/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBdEVCIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--d1de41531006031e0a7eceedccfb297b7bb9b20b/Footprints%20On%20Our%20Land%20Mock%20Up.png" filename="Footprints On Our Land Mock Up.png" filesize="2530292" width="2000" height="1300" previewable="true" presentation="gallery" caption="."></action-text-attachment></div><div><a href="http://www.south-african-homeschool-curriculum.com/literature-based-curriculum.html"><strong>Footprints on Our Land</strong></a> is the best-selling literature-based curriculum centered around South African historical fiction and is aimed at children between the ages of 7-14 years. It is a multi-age level unit study beginning in 1488 when Bartholomew Dias rounded the Cape and ends in the early 1900s just after the South African War. But it is not only a history curriculum! Being a unit study, the lesson plans are built around the children’s literature, and includes a wide range of topics which cover geography, biology and nature study, science, language arts, cooking, art, crafts, technology and bible study. This non-consumable programme can be used comfortably with many children over 2 years. Be sure to watch our video on the video tab about this program and the exciting hands on and discussion way of learning we offer.<br><br><em>“We are doing Footprints on Our Land. You cannot go wrong. My boys LOVE the stories. And you can research the topics as much as you want. There are no time limits, you work at your own pace. Soon we will be building a mini replica of Bartholomew Dias caravel. It’s very hands on… definitely our favourite part of our homeschool day.”</em> ~ Candice S.<strong> </strong><br><br></div><div><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSI9Z2lkOi8vZXZlbnRzLXBsYXRmb3JtL0FjdGl2ZVN0b3JhZ2U6OkJsb2IvNDY5P2V4cGlyZXNfaW4GOwBUSSIMcHVycG9zZQY7AFRJIg9hdHRhY2hhYmxlBjsAVEkiD2V4cGlyZXNfYXQGOwBUMA==--0df0c2f52d5d21d94f9e7e5593f4de9796c70d75" content-type="image/png" url="http://homeschoolexpo.africa/files/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBdFVCIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--b8d26a69593d40ea1680d4b5b7ae34806aa3bdd1/3.png" filename="3.png" filesize="53993" width="2050" height="780" previewable="true" presentation="gallery" caption="."></action-text-attachment><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSI-Z2lkOi8vZXZlbnRzLXBsYXRmb3JtL0FjdGl2ZVN0b3JhZ2U6OkJsb2IvMTAzMz9leHBpcmVzX2luBjsAVEkiDHB1cnBvc2UGOwBUSSIPYXR0YWNoYWJsZQY7AFRJIg9leHBpcmVzX2F0BjsAVDA=--7a767a2f38e388521205e05acca19ba74705970f" content-type="image/png" url="http://homeschoolexpo.africa/files/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBZ2tFIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--3d301049fbff42a362620babd4bc505b953d3724/Footprints%20Into%20the%2021st%20Century%20Mock%20Up%20(Final).png" filename="Footprints Into the 21st Century Mock Up (Final).png" filesize="2969685" width="2000" height="1300" previewable="true" presentation="gallery" caption="Footprints into the 21st Century"></action-text-attachment></div><div><a href="http://www.south-african-homeschool-curriculum.com/high-school-homeschool-curriculum.html"><strong>Footprints into the 21st Century</strong></a> is an original and uniquely South African high school homeschool unit study curriculum, which presents teens with some of the best books that portray this era in the history of our country. It includes historical fiction, poetry, reference books as well as biographies of people who contributed to the events of the century. It is up to date with recent history and includes the ever-changing South African faces in politics, the drama of the State Capture Report, the pain of the Angolan Bush War, the Woman’s March to Pretoria along with the history that we know – or thought we knew – of the Apartheid Era and the Freedom Struggle and more. Be sure to watch our video on the video tab about this program and the way your teen can gently be encouraged to take over their education goals.<br><br><em>“I’ve used and re-used our </em><a href="http://www.south-african-homeschool-curriculum.com/high-school-homeschool-curriculum.html"><em>Footprints into the 21st Century</em></a><em> three times with each of my high schoolers. It has been a unique journey and approach with each child, one I highly recommend. It has been a delight to read of other’s perspectives and experiences through the wonderful collection of literature, and I find a renewed understanding of our history.” ~ Nadene Esterhuizen </em><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSI9Z2lkOi8vZXZlbnRzLXBsYXRmb3JtL0FjdGl2ZVN0b3JhZ2U6OkJsb2IvNDcxP2V4cGlyZXNfaW4GOwBUSSIMcHVycG9zZQY7AFRJIg9hdHRhY2hhYmxlBjsAVEkiD2V4cGlyZXNfYXQGOwBUMA==--78dfe9a05dfed52f1ef7eaf3dcbaa2672ea6ff38" content-type="image/png" url="http://homeschoolexpo.africa/files/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBdGNCIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--089c3da2bd62e1b2972dede9aab170d8df3787f2/Little%20Footprints%204-8%20year%20olds%20South%20Africa%20in%20picture%20story%20books.png" filename="Little Footprints 4-8 year olds South Africa in picture story books.png" filesize="42246" width="2050" height="780" previewable="true" presentation="gallery" caption="."></action-text-attachment></div><div><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSI9Z2lkOi8vZXZlbnRzLXBsYXRmb3JtL0FjdGl2ZVN0b3JhZ2U6OkJsb2IvNDcwP2V4cGlyZXNfaW4GOwBUSSIMcHVycG9zZQY7AFRJIg9hdHRhY2hhYmxlBjsAVEkiD2V4cGlyZXNfYXQGOwBUMA==--e8e0db77aaf3722a36c8fff22b4645079968ea23" content-type="image/png" url="http://homeschoolexpo.africa/files/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBdFlCIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--18c4dd29e26341efab423f614bb70547c54dc7e4/Voetspore%20Mock%20Up.png" filename="Voetspore Mock Up.png" filesize="2473355" width="2000" height="1300" previewable="true" presentation="gallery" caption="."></action-text-attachment>Voetspore is gebore uit die voortdurende versoeke van Afrikaanse tuisonderwysouers om toegang te kry tot 'n Charlotte Mason-styl styl van inderrig, met behulp van bronne uit Suid-Afrika, ‘lewende’ boeke en lewenservaring. Oor die jare heen na talle tuisonderwys-ekspo's het ons gesien hoe beperk die opsies vir Afrikaanse gesinne is wat daarna streef om hul kinders 'n ‘lewende’ onderrig soos "Footprints" te bied, maar om dit in hul moedertaal te doen. <br><br>Voetspore kan vergelyk word met 'n ekspedisie deur Suid-Afrika. Dit gaan nie oor die vertrek en n wedloop om op 'n spesifieke tyd by ń spesifieke bestemming te kom nie; dit gaan eerder oor die genot van die rit: stop om 'n onderwerp te verken wat jul belangstelling boei, gaan maak 'n draai om 'n minder bekende trekpleister te besoek, talm op 'n plek van ongerepte skoonheid en verwonder jul oor die feit dat dit ons erfenis, ons mense, ons Suid-Afrika is! <br><br>Om hierdie rede sal die hoeveelheid tyd wat aan elke boek bestee word, wissel. U word aangemoedig om dieper te gaan delf en enige onderwerp wat u kind se belangstelling boei of wat volgens u meer aandag verdien, in meer besonderhede te ondersoek. Daar is twee dele. Deel 1 handel oor die geskiedenis van die eerste mense wat in ons land gewoon het, nl. die Khoi-groepe, tot die Groot Trek en kyk na die Nederlandse, Franse en Britse setlaars en die botsings wat plaasgevind het toe mense die binneland ingetrek het. Deel 2 handel oor die ontdekking van goud en diamante, neem jou deur die Eerste en Tweede Wêreldoorloë, die Angolese bosoorlog en die vryheidstryd tot vandag toe. <br><br>Elk van die 12 afdelings bevat ook 'n afdeling vir natuurwetenskap. Dit is spesifiek vir die verskillende natuurlike biome wat in Suid-Afrika voorkom. Jy besoek die Nama-Karoo, gaan swem met visse en seevoëls, en ontdek die skeepswrakke langs ons kus. Jy sal vleilande, moeraslande en grasvelde besoek tydens jou reis deur ons land. Jy sal ook kyk na Suid-Afrika se erfenisterreine en ons nasionale parke. Ons hoop dat dit julle ook sal aanmoedig om in ons pragtige land rond te reis.</div><div><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSI9Z2lkOi8vZXZlbnRzLXBsYXRmb3JtL0FjdGl2ZVN0b3JhZ2U6OkJsb2IvNjUxP2V4cGlyZXNfaW4GOwBUSSIMcHVycG9zZQY7AFRJIg9hdHRhY2hhYmxlBjsAVEkiD2V4cGlyZXNfYXQGOwBUMA==--0e381e37a43377bb04ae7ed6890d20ee0907d5bc" content-type="image/png" url="http://homeschoolexpo.africa/files/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBb3NDIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--3e79523901687289f31b1e53cf36f3efa3583080/Coming%20December%202020.png" filename="Coming December 2020.png" filesize="815977" width="940" height="788" previewable="true" presentation="gallery" caption="Voetspore - Desember 2020"></action-text-attachment><br><br></div>	Company	14	20