370	about_exhibitor	<div><strong>MiniChess builds SMART MINDS for the 21st Century  <br></strong><br></div><div>MiniChess is a Game-changer for 21st Century education - using award-winning Play-innovations to develop critical skills from the early ages, to empower our children for a fast-changing future: focusing on smart thinking skills (including entrepreneurial thinking), resilient socio-emotional tools &amp; a solid understanding of Mathematics- and STEM-skills… It unlocks our children’s potential with those things machines cannot do – creativity, forward thinking, strategic planning, empathy, and much more! </div><div>The inter-disciplinary, neuro-based and fun approach to teaching delivers excellent and long-term benefits. Blended teaching platforms are used, including live classes (MiniChess Clubs), a stunning Online Platform, MiniChess Festivals and Tournaments. Amongst many international awards, we recently pocketed the prestigious <strong>Holistic Education Innovation Excellence Award 2020!</strong></div><div>More info at <a href="www.minichess.co.za%20">www.minichess.co.za</a> and/or <a href="https://www.facebook.com/minichess.co.za/">https://www.facebook.com/minichess.co.za/<br></a><br><strong>1.</strong>       <strong>University Studies and Participation<br></strong><br></div><div>The University of Pretoria performed a study on the impact of the MiniChess program on School-readiness &amp; correcting early developmental backlogs. The study results below illustrate the impact (%) on holistic development, doing the MiniChess program at a test school, once per week over a 4-month period:<br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSI-Z2lkOi8vZXZlbnRzLXBsYXRmb3JtL0FjdGl2ZVN0b3JhZ2U6OkJsb2IvMTYzOD9leHBpcmVzX2luBjsAVEkiDHB1cnBvc2UGOwBUSSIPYXR0YWNoYWJsZQY7AFRJIg9leHBpcmVzX2F0BjsAVDA=--739108b5ec9b58b454dc04e7a5163f1b9ff90313" content-type="image/png" url="http://homeschoolexpo.africa/files/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBbVlHIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--e01a23cf00ad60fd433acbdb051c23ab872ef450/Capture.PNG" filename="Capture.PNG" filesize="13992" width="641" height="260" previewable="true" presentation="gallery" caption="University of Pretoria Study"></action-text-attachment>The MiniChess program has reached 250+ schools in SA, 9 African countries, New Zealand, USA, Beijing and Germany, with 100,000+ learners benefitting. Sponsors and universities have measured the impact of this play-innovation program for 21st Century relevance: University of Johannesburg study-results showed much-improved number-sense (adding &amp; subtracting), graph-reading and pattern-recognition in maths, as well as much-improved social-skills, concentration, problem-solving &amp; critical skills in general. Rural sponsored schools illustrated their math-average improving to 70%+ per grade, math pass-rates to improve from below 50% to above 90% in all classes, and showing an OVER-ALL academic improvement of 40%+ after implementing MiniChess from the early years - with the biggest impact in mathematics-scores (up to 70% improvement in year 1 at disadvantaged schools).<br><br><strong>1.</strong>       <strong>Local &amp; International acclaim<br></strong><br></div><div>Marisa van der Merwe, developer of the MiniChess program, won the Shoprite Checkers Women of the Year Award 2012, category Education (Top educational-program 2012). It is also accredited by CHESSA, FIDE and is considered a “GAME-CHANGER” by many schools using MiniChess for Early Childhood Development and in the Foundation phase of the Primary School.</div><div>The MiniChess program originated in SA, is translated into 7 languages and Trademarked on 5 Continents.</div><div>MiniChess was invited to present at various internationally recognised Education Conferences: </div><div>§  Women in the World (New York, 2013), </div><div>§  The Association for Childhood Education International (Vancouver, 2014), </div><div>§  London Chess &amp; Math Conferences (2013, 2014 &amp; 2015), </div><div>§  WISE (World Innovation Summit on Education, Qatar, 2014) – attended by 120+ countries, where MiniChess was nominated for an innovation award. <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_RJpbc7Fusg&amp;list=FLijkykyJzpxW4xbaNf6pVFw">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_RJpbc7Fusg&amp;list=FLijkykyJzpxW4xbaNf6pVFw</a></div><div>§  MiniChess also co-presented at the 10th Global Visual Literacy Conference in Lisbon (2015), of which a publication was included in an e-book by Oxford University in 2016, </div><div>§  Key-note speaker at the International ECD-Conference in Bishkek, Central Asia, </div><div>§  EduWeek 2016 &amp; 2017 in Johannesburg and Cape Town, South Africa.  MiniChess won the “<strong>EduWeek ECD Supplier of the Year 2018</strong>” award!<br><br></div><div><strong>2.</strong>       <strong>Kasparov Chess Foundation Endorsement<br></strong><br></div><div>The Kasparov Chess Foundation-Africa endorses the MiniChess program, and also incorporates the program in their roll-outs in various countries.  Grandmaster Garry Kasparov, ex-World Chess Champion, calls MiniChess “<strong><em>the most scientific program in the world, linking chess with Education</em></strong>”.</div><div>The Kasparov-MiniChess mobile game was launched in 2015 on all mobile platforms, towards enriching the MiniChess in-class program. <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=PPXgoLLO5Mg">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=PPXgoLLO5Mg</a></div><div><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=uU_dpukQvDY">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=uU_dpukQvDY<br></a><br></div><div><strong>3.</strong>       <strong>Collaboration for long-term education-empowerment – to enrich in-school curricula &amp; the Young Leaders of the future!<br></strong><br></div><div>MiniChess is implemented in self-paying communities through in-community partners, AND ALSO in disadvantaged communities in collaboration with The Entrust Foundation (an NPO), community- and business-leaders, as well as other NGO/PBO’s, towards sustainable long-term, quality-based, education-benefit and skills development for in-community entrepreneurship. </div><div><strong> </strong></div><div><strong>Let us take hands - harnessing the most powerful energy in the world, HUMAN TALENT, for success in the 21st Century! </strong></div><div><strong>Give your child the winning advantage of the future, TODAY.</strong></div><div><strong>Team MiniChess<br></strong><br></div><div> </div>	Company	51	2020-09-29 14:07:06.386822	2020-10-07 09:02:23.686081
