363	about_exhibitor	<div>The homeschool way of life ushered owner and founder of Cubits Kids Edu and Diversio Learning Academy on a path of discovering her love of learning again. As an extreme researcher, homeschooling has given her the best of all the things she loves: books, technology, helping others, and creating beautiful and inspiring learning experiences for her children and, yes, research! She started Cubits Kids Edu in 2018 as a platform to share homeschool news, curriculum reviews, information and as a curriculum supplier. Since then, she assisted numerous families in designing an educational path for themselves – tailored to each individual but taking mom as the primary facilitator in consideration. She realized there are deep-rooted concerns parents have when they come to her for advice and consultation, and founded Diversio Learning Academy as a way to assist homeschooling families to have a peaceful experience when educating at home. The approach is different though because at <strong>Diversio Learning Academy (DLA) </strong>we don't teach kids... Yes, let that sink in. We "teach" adults; the parents how to make their family's home learning journey not only memorable but how to make it worthwhile from the early years to graduation.<br><br></div><div><strong><em>We equip the parents to make the best choices for their kids and to take huge leaps when planning their teenagers' middle and high school educational plan but allowing their children to thrive.</em></strong><strong> We do not provide a box with a curriculum and send you on your way. </strong>We invite you to come visit us as a family, as mom alone or just parents and give us the tools to assist you in planning an eclectic educational path that will excite, intrigue and involve each member of the family. We know that every family is different, we know that each child's needs in a family differ from their siblings and their parents' expectations. We listen, we hear, we calm fears and take a deep breath - together. Then we let the creativity flow and provide a personal educational plan. A plan where parents working from home or with kids from all ages can have time to facilitate some courses themselves, have other courses facilitated through virtual, digital and streaming options while they earn an income and take care of perhaps a grandparent. <em>At Diversio Learning Academy we know how challenging the demands of everyday life, work, business, combined with your child's education can be!</em> We know, because we are living that life and have experienced the impact of overload and not having support but we have also experienced the joy and freedom of using a personal educational plan to allow our children to grow their strengths and weaknesses. Diversio Learning Academy supports the whole family through their homeschool journey, we include the youngest members of the family, the dad's who often feel disconnected and even the grandparents when they play a vital role in the family dynamic.<br><br></div><div><strong><em>At our core beliefs, we value the importance of meeting every child where they are at. This translates into the diverse educational needs of a child which must be met in order to equip them for future success.  From there the name Diversio Learning Academy - concentrating efforts towards not one method but various methods to gain the greatest realization of each individual. Artists, dancers, high academics, teens with their hearts set on missionary work, struggling learners, children with learning disabilities, or highly gifted learners; everyone can be accommodated in the educational plan which leads to the American High School Diploma. </em></strong><br><br><strong>At Diversio Learning Academy, learning diversity is pursued. <br></strong><br></div><blockquote><blockquote><strong><em>"I want to thank Diversio Learning; especially Stephané for the well thought out and thorough planning guide. She asked various questions about my son; including his strengths, weaknesses, interests, etc. She used the answers to compile a unique plan, tailor-made for him. She gave us several options for each of her recommendations with links for us to peruse and try before deciding which direction he wants to pursue.  She then followed this up with a phone call in which she went through each part, step by step explaining her suggestions and why she felt that they would work for him, answering all my questions along the way. <br>I further had the reassurance that if at any time we were in doubt or if we had questions, she was a phone call or an email away. I would not want to make this journey with anyone else." ~Alene, mom to 3 homeschoolers, might be new to the American Diploma route but she is not new to homeschooling. With her remarkable thirst for knowledge, she provided possibilities for her oldest to still achieve success, despite professional opinions telling her otherwise.</em></strong></blockquote></blockquote><div><strong><br>Our future plans </strong>include weekend break-out camps for new homeschoolers or families needing a revival in their journey. <br>We look forward to hosting matric graduation ceremonies for our DLA seniors (Gr. 12) as well as week-long Divergent DLA camps for the whole family. These camps will involve everyone in the family, and though it might feel like a holiday all activities and workshops are focused on learning experiences which allows the development of each person in different directions. Experiences which will challenge or hone skills with high schoolers being able to use any or all of the activities as part of their credits needed towards graduation or in their portfolio of evidence. Activities and workshops will range from archery, aerial fitness, health and nutrition for teenagers to three-day workshops in journalism, introduction to computer-aided design, and for our junior and senior (Gr11 and 12) learners a workshop on writing their college/university application essay. Nature intensives will focus on natural history courses which will include stargazing, botany, geology and nature photography. Mom will be able to attend planning workshops, a book club, sessions on how to create integrated learning experiences by using art, music, and games to teach various subjects at once. Dad will get the time to meet other homeschooling dads, they will be able to show off their talents by taking part in either the kitchen, entertainment or physics of fishing challenges. Evenings will be a time of age-old story-telling, music and overall a time where the focus is on connecting with every member of the family. As families you will make new friends, explore the beauty of the area and find encouragement, you will leave the camp feeling relaxed, connected, and excited to continue on your path.<br><br><strong>Our hope is to meet all of our Diversio Learning Academy families and establish real connections through these camps, which will enrich their lives and support their journey.</strong></div>	Company	50	2020-09-29 12:17:41.418754	2020-10-04 13:11:39.757301
