68	introduction	<div><br></div><div><strong><em>Welcome to Imperial International College (IIC)!</em></strong></div><div><br>We at IIC believe that it is <em>vitally important </em>for students to <strong>Learn How To Learn</strong>.<br><br>In our experience, mainstream schools often have a spoon-feeding approach to learning, and when those students graduate and enter a university or working environment, they are unprepared for the expectations placed on them, and are unable to take initiative and figure out problems for themselves.<br><br>Therefore, we do not approach our online distance learning in this way. Rather, we expect students to grapple with the material in their textbooks, follow the Lesson Sets, watch any videos or complete any activities that may be included, and contact their tutor once they have done all they can to understand a concept but are still needing some additional guidance.<br><br>Rather than our tutors "teaching" concepts to students, they are there to offer guidance, and help students to figure out the concepts/topics for themselves.<br><br>This is a very important life-skill, and sets students up for success as they move out of a school environment and into the real world. It teaches them to think critically, to approach issues with a mindset that is willing to try and figure the problem out, and to know that they are capable of creating solutions for themselves.<br><br>Read more about our <strong>Products and Services</strong> to find out how we try to facilitate online learning.</div>	Company	23	2020-09-09 14:09:36.445726	2020-09-29 13:19:44.068722
