69	products_and_services	<div><br></div><h1><strong>An Overview of Our Offering:</strong></h1><div><br>We are an <strong>online, distance learning institution</strong> and we offer tutor support for students around the world who are wanting to complete their Cambridge International GCSE (Gr10/11) and AS-Level (Gr12) exams.<br>Students from all across the globe can write the Cambridge qualifications, which are <strong>recognized and accepted by universities worldwide</strong>.<br><br>IIC is not a registered Cambridge centre, as Cambridge do not yet register purely distance-learning institutes, however all of our material aligns to the various Cambridge syllabi and fully prepares students to write their final International GCSE (often referred to as IG) and AS-Level (often referred to as AS) exams.<br><br>We offer tutor support via an online learning platform called Moodle, and each subject that a student enrolls in has its own <strong>course page</strong>, with a dedicated <strong>tutor </strong>who can be contacted for help if the student is struggling to understand a concept.<br><br>These course pages include a <strong>timetable </strong>that shows what content will be covered in the textbook as well as the due dates for each Assessment, which test sections of the syllabus, for example three or four chapters at a time. Additionally, each Assessment has its own <strong>Lesson Set</strong>, which walks students through their textbook, step-by-step, specifying which pages and exercises need to be completed, as well as any learning outcomes that may apply to that content. <br><br>For most subjects, there are <strong>videos </strong>that expand upon the content covered in the textbook. There may also be <strong>activities </strong>to be completed, and in some cases, <strong>quizzes </strong>that test a student's knowledge of the work they have just covered in bite-sized chunks.<br>All of this <strong>enrichment material</strong> is designed to broaden a student's understanding of each concept, and if they are still unsure of how to approach a question or apply a concept, their subject tutor is an email away.<br><br>Over and above these activities and videos, we facilitate continuous assessment through each of our courses and each subject has on average 12 major <strong>Assessments</strong>, the final few of which are actual <strong>past papers</strong>. Each of these Assessments is <strong>marked </strong>by our tutors and comments and guidance are provided. <br><br><br></div><h1><strong>Our Courses:</strong></h1><div><br>Both our International GCSE (Gr 10/11) and AS-Level (Gr 12) courses are <strong>either 12 months or 18 months</strong> <strong>long</strong>, depending on a student’s academic background.<br><br>Students who enter at a grade 10 level (i.e. after completing grade 9 or equivalent), who choose the 18 month course option, will take 3 years to obtain their Matric Certificate provided they complete all of the course material in the allotted time and pass the required exams as intended.<br><br>The 12 month course option is available for students who wish to fast-track their studies, or who have perhaps completed a portion of their syllabus for that particular grade and wish to write sooner than 18 months from the date of enrollment.<br><br>We have <strong>two intakes per year</strong>, one in <strong>January </strong>and another in <strong>July</strong>. This is possible as the IG and AS examinations are held worldwide in <strong>May/June</strong> every year and also <strong>October/November</strong> every year.<br><br>As such a student who begins an 18 month course in January will write exams in the following year’s May/June session while a student who begin an 18 month course with us in July will write their exams in the October/November session of the following year. A student who begins a 12 month course with us in January will write exams in the October/November session of that same year, while a student beginning a 12-month course with us in July will write their exams in the May/June session of the following year.<br><br><br></div><h1><strong>Subject Options:</strong></h1><div><br>We offer a <strong>variety of subjects</strong> at an International GCSE level and AS-Level.<br><br></div><blockquote><strong>TO FIND OUT MORE ABOUT OUR SUBJECT OFFERING</strong>, please view our <a href="https://iic-online.com/iic-subject-list/"><strong>Subject List</strong>.</a></blockquote><div><br><br></div><h1><strong>Our Pricing Structure:</strong></h1><div><br>Our tutor support is offered on a <strong>subscription basis</strong>, meaning that you are only paying for the support received each month, rather than paying a bulk cost for the entire course upfront. <br>In this manner, if you wish to discontinue (or reduce) your support through us, you would simply cancel your subscription (or perhaps downgrade it to only one or two subjects) and you will have only paid for what you have used.<br><br><strong>Your academic journey with us will consist of three main costs:</strong><br><br><em>1. Tutor Support Subscription</em><strong><br><br></strong>We charge a <strong>subscription fee</strong> for each subject that you enroll for. You register once for the number of subjects you require and pay 1 month subscription upfront.<br><br></div><ul><li>If you choose the 18-month course option, you are charged the listed amount over a period of 15 months, which comes to a total of 16 payments including the upfront payment.</li><li>If you choose the 12-month course option, you are charged the listed amount over a period of 9 months, which comes to a total of 10 payments including the upfront payment.</li><li>For either option, you will have completed paying for your course before you start writing your exams.</li><li>You are able to <strong>increase or decrease the number of subjects</strong> during your studies if you need to</li></ul><div><em>2. Text Book Costs</em><strong><br><br></strong>After registering for our tutor support you will receive access to our <strong>booklist </strong>for the subjects that you have ordered. Once you have the booklist you are welcome to <strong>order your textbooks through your supplier of choice</strong>. Two recommendations are takealot.co.za and loot.co.za.<br><br><em>3. Examination Fees</em><strong><br></strong><br></div><div>These fees are <strong>once-off and are paid to the examination venue </strong>through whom you choose to write your exams. You will only need to pay these fees about <strong>5 months before your exams </strong>(w<em>hich are held in either May/June or October/November each year</em>). These costs can be confirmed through your examination venue of choice.<br><br></div><blockquote><strong>TO FIND OUT MORE ABOUT OUR PRICING STRUCTURE</strong>, please visit<strong> </strong>our <a href="https://iic-online.com/pricing/"><strong>Pricing Page</strong></a>.</blockquote><div><br><br></div><div><br></div><h1><strong>What About University?</strong></h1><div><br></div><blockquote><strong>TO FIND OUT MORE ABOUT FINAL EXAMINATIONS AND UNIVERSITY ENTRANCE</strong>, please view our guidelines on <a href="https://iic-online.com/exams-and-university/"><strong>Exams and University</strong></a>.</blockquote><div><br><br><br></div><h1><strong>How to Apply:</strong></h1><div><br></div><div>Once you are comfortable with the costs of studying through I.I.C. and have an idea of subject choices, you can begin our application process. <br><br>This involves both a <strong>form </strong>that you fill out and <strong>admission exams</strong> that you need to email back to <a href="mailto:admissions@iic-online.com">admissions@iic-online.com</a>.<br><br>The International GCSE (Gr10/11) admission exams can be found on our website as downloads just above the application form. <br>The AS-level (Gr12) admission exam consists of past papers. We will send you links to these once we receive your completed application form <br><br></div><blockquote><strong>TO GET STARTED WITH YOUR ENROLLMENT PROCESS, </strong>follow this link to<strong> </strong><a href="https://iic-online.com/apply-to-study/"><strong>Apply to Study Now!</strong></a></blockquote>	Company	23	2020-09-09 14:09:36.449346	2020-09-29 14:06:09.64176
