392	workshop_facilitator_info	<div>Wendy Young is a veteran homeschooler who home educated her children all the way. She is well known in the South African homeschool community as the author of Footprints on Our Land homeschool curricula. She is a seasoned homeschool blogger and mom of 4 homeschool grads. Her 3 eldest have completed their tertiary education and are gainfully employed. Her youngest is currently studying engineering at university.<br>Wendy now offers personalized consultations for new and old homeschoolers. Read more below.</div><div><br></div><h1>Homeschooling Consultation by Wendy Young</h1><div><br>When you start out on your home education journey you could perhaps end up in one of the positions below:</div><div><br></div><div>Overwhelmed by the curriculum choices</div><div>Unsure of how to begin</div><div>Needing “how to” help</div><div><br></div><div>Or if you have been home educating your children for a while you may need input for high school, school leaving, or unmotivated children for example.</div><div><br></div><div>Perhaps your children have specific needs due to neurodiversity like Aspergers (ASD), sensory issues, demand avoidance, or learning difficulties like Dyslexia, ADHD, or Apraxia.</div><div><br></div><div>After homeschooling my own children all the way for more than 20years I have either experienced these challenges myself or counseled parents in those positions. </div><div><br></div><div>If you find yourself in any of these situations, I can help!</div><div><br></div><div>You and I can book an online or in-person hour-long consultation. At this time I will go through a brief education history with you. You will explain what your concerns are and together we will come up with a workable solution.</div><div><br></div><div>After your session, I will send you detailed feedback as well as an optional 3-year curriculum plan tailor-made for your family’s needs.</div><div><br><br></div><div><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSI-Z2lkOi8vZXZlbnRzLXBsYXRmb3JtL0FjdGl2ZVN0b3JhZ2U6OkJsb2IvMTA4OD9leHBpcmVzX2luBjsAVEkiDHB1cnBvc2UGOwBUSSIPYXR0YWNoYWJsZQY7AFRJIg9leHBpcmVzX2F0BjsAVDA=--0a88c6700e8ca5fd0db4c70f9c02daa9187b239c" content-type="image/jpeg" url="http://www.homeschoolexpo.africa/files/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBa0FFIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--0d4249a0d3715a377006e8392248262b67fe34f1/Home%20Education%20Consultations%20(2).jpg" filename="Home Education Consultations (2).jpg" filesize="1433647" width="1181" height="1181" previewable="true" presentation="gallery" caption="Home Education Consultation"></action-text-attachment>Contact me to book your appointment.<br>Email: footprintsonourland@mweb.co.za</div><div><br><br></div><div>Testimonies:</div><div><br></div><div>“My daughter feels empowered as she now knows with clarity the route we are following  and the end goal is clear She is motivated and less anxious. All in all a happy teenager.” Colleen, Cape Town</div><div><br><br></div><div>“I am homeschooling my two youngest boys, aged 16 and 14, and had been doing so for 3 years when I decided to meet with Wendy to clarify the way forward with regards to honing down the subjects, finding the relevant resources, and dealing with challenges with a very inattentive, unmotivated teenager. It was great, and I cannot recommend her enough. Very often, when you're in the 'trenches' you cannot see objectively, and she was able to confirm or guide the choices I was considering. It is invaluable to get advice from someone whose family has not only survived (! we all have those days) but THRIVED in homeschooling. All that we chatted about, she noted down and sent back to me in point form, broken down in time segments, with goals outlined, resources provided, and clarity is given. Brilliant! Highly recommend!” Lea, Cape Town</div><div><br><br></div><div>“We had been thinking of homeschooling our children for a while, but when we were thrust into it, it was a different story to what I’d imagined. Our school was very organized in terms of sending work through for the kids, but I wasn’t coping with three of them in different grades, and work coming through on different platforms and had to make a plan to reach sanity quickly. I really appreciated our zoom meeting – you immediately answered so many of my questions in terms of what I could do (they will possibly still return to mainstream schooling so we need to keep that in the back of our minds as well), how to structure the day, how to work with the different ages and a myriad of other questions I had. Your swift follows up email, pertaining to information we had discussed, as well as the full zoom recording really made me feel that this is something we can do! </div><div>Thank you – we are still finding our feet, but feeling so much calmer about all of it, and really looking forward to the rest of this year!” Di,  Knysna</div><div><br></div><div>“Thank you for the time you invested in sharing your experience and knowledge with me. Your feedback gave me confirmation for many choices I was making. The first piece of advice that stood out for me was when you suggested I step back from a situation and ask myself is my child struggling with understanding a concept or is it a bad attitude I am dealing with. This is the beauty of homeschooling, where we can slow down and work together to cross any bridges. </div><div>Secondly, when you sent your breakdown of hoops to jump to reach the end goal you had added "learners license at 17", this small addition was a reminder that although we can move slowly we have still got to keep going as there will be milestones the child will want to achieve. </div><div>Lastly, you suggested I keep a progress journal so we could keep track of our family's growth which helps keep us confident with our journey without having to worry about what everyone else is achieving.  So again I wish to thank you for your willingness to share your ideas and many years of experience.” Tracy, JHB</div>	Workshop	4	2020-09-30 13:49:01.862261	2020-10-08 17:50:32.241044
