135	about_exhibitor	<h1>An EZ history ...</h1><div><br></div><div>Having taught Accounting and Business Economics (now Business Studies) for a number of years, both in the classroom and privately, I soon realised that there was a gaping need for material that learners would find easy and fun to work with. As a result, EZ Learn Books was born in 2001, with the creation of A+ Accounting study guides aimed at making the basic concepts easy to learn, including basic notes, examples and revision tests. EZ Business Economics Grade 12 was the next to be introduced, as I realised that pupils and teachers found the EZ Learn style easy to work with, and of course Business Economics guides for grades 10 and 11 soon followed. With the advent of the new, revised curriculum, text books for Economic &amp; Management Sciences were soon launched as well. <br><br>It soon became apparent that the Accounting study guides needed to be upgraded to text books, and these were revamped and expanded into the popular EZ Learn guides they are today, characterised by fun activities, explanations that are easy to understand, relevant case studies and articles, worked examples, exercises covering a variety of skills and ranging from easy to challenging, and of course tests and exams for revision purposes. <br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSI-Z2lkOi8vZXZlbnRzLXBsYXRmb3JtL0FjdGl2ZVN0b3JhZ2U6OkJsb2IvMjA5OD9leHBpcmVzX2luBjsAVEkiDHB1cnBvc2UGOwBUSSIPYXR0YWNoYWJsZQY7AFRJIg9leHBpcmVzX2F0BjsAVDA=--56286aabdde3a81313f5bc5a5806acb4ae3857f5" content-type="image/jpeg" url="http://homeschoolexpo.africa/files/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBaklJIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--5768c1c4fd493e3edd5b4e5cb0061a16aa0ab7de/EZ%20Learn%20Acc.jpg" filename="EZ Learn Acc.jpg" filesize="322766" width="1514" height="706" previewable="true" presentation="gallery" caption="The EZ Learn Accounting range"></action-text-attachment><br><br>In 2004 permission was obtained from both the Department of Education and the Independent Examinations Board to republish past examination papers, and the EZ Revision guides were born. More than just a collation of exam papers, these include detailed study plans, crash course or summary notes, exam questions divided into the different sections covered, and complete answers with helpful hints. This dynamic combination has proved incredibly popular with students and teachers alike.<br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSI-Z2lkOi8vZXZlbnRzLXBsYXRmb3JtL0FjdGl2ZVN0b3JhZ2U6OkJsb2IvMjA5OT9leHBpcmVzX2luBjsAVEkiDHB1cnBvc2UGOwBUSSIPYXR0YWNoYWJsZQY7AFRJIg9leHBpcmVzX2F0BjsAVDA=--a2c2927220d00bb4a0a7ab0df132ee0211ae0bbd" content-type="image/jpeg" url="http://homeschoolexpo.africa/files/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBak1JIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--1e9463bff41ed6474f8b351c325d5eab8c2cf8d6/EZ%20Rev%20Acc.jpg" filename="EZ Rev Acc.jpg" filesize="332204" width="1498" height="706" previewable="true" presentation="gallery" caption="The EZ Revision Accounting range"></action-text-attachment></div><div><br>The Fun EMS guides were launched in 2012 for the new CAPS requirements, and were very well received. Combined with access to free additional resources via Google Classrooms, EZ Learn continues to keep up to date with changes in the online learning environment. Self-marking Excel tests and quizzes, PowerPoint presentation slides and electronic solutions all contribute to a better teaching and learning experience. <br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSI-Z2lkOi8vZXZlbnRzLXBsYXRmb3JtL0FjdGl2ZVN0b3JhZ2U6OkJsb2IvMjEwMD9leHBpcmVzX2luBjsAVEkiDHB1cnBvc2UGOwBUSSIPYXR0YWNoYWJsZQY7AFRJIg9leHBpcmVzX2F0BjsAVDA=--407b492babaf74b10b7c734fffdeabd8614d39e3" content-type="image/jpeg" url="http://homeschoolexpo.africa/files/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBalFJIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--e6e344563dfb615bb93574f46d8186d1b9df1e07/Fun%20EMS.jpg" filename="Fun EMS.jpg" filesize="349778" width="1474" height="1030" previewable="true" presentation="gallery" caption="The Fun EMS range"></action-text-attachment></div><div><br>EZ Learn's YouTube channel has since added another dimension to the EZ teaching solution, with QR codes in the guides and links in the Classrooms providing direct access to relevant videos on different topics. <br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSI-Z2lkOi8vZXZlbnRzLXBsYXRmb3JtL0FjdGl2ZVN0b3JhZ2U6OkJsb2IvMjEwMT9leHBpcmVzX2luBjsAVEkiDHB1cnBvc2UGOwBUSSIPYXR0YWNoYWJsZQY7AFRJIg9leHBpcmVzX2F0BjsAVDA=--d2d077e9f9fc8ccf3b109ac1529ebc5c093f1da4" content-type="image/jpeg" url="http://homeschoolexpo.africa/files/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBalVJIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--27935893ac043d6edf33bf78dd3c4c377956fbbe/EZ%20YouTube.jpg" filename="EZ YouTube.jpg" filesize="270089" width="2408" height="804" previewable="true" presentation="gallery" caption="EZ Learn's YouTube channel"></action-text-attachment></div><div><br>In 2017 I ventured into discovering the Cambridge curriculum, and have thoroughly enjoyed the juxtaposition of this and the IEB curriculum to which I was used to. Both have their strengths, and each add a different dimension to commercial subjects. As I gained confidence teaching students IGCSE, AS and A Level, I started developing notes and arranging resource material in Google Classrooms. These are now being developed further, and I hope to launch a set of EZ guides for Cambridge in the near future. <br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSI-Z2lkOi8vZXZlbnRzLXBsYXRmb3JtL0FjdGl2ZVN0b3JhZ2U6OkJsb2IvMjEwMj9leHBpcmVzX2luBjsAVEkiDHB1cnBvc2UGOwBUSSIPYXR0YWNoYWJsZQY7AFRJIg9leHBpcmVzX2F0BjsAVDA=--c58a0710e441e5afa3fa071c475de17e3dcde90e" content-type="image/jpeg" url="http://homeschoolexpo.africa/files/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBallJIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--d8067fb7b11c7bb614abe66c6f262ae5f3cdf15f/EZ%20Classrooms.jpg" filename="EZ Classrooms.jpg" filesize="107566" width="1168" height="364" previewable="true" presentation="gallery" caption="EZ Classrooms for Cambridge"></action-text-attachment></div><div><br>2020 brought an entirely new perspective to the sphere of education. Luckily, I had already dabbled in flip-teaching and a variety of online teaching tools since 2010, and so EZ Learn was well placed to assist teachers with ideas of how to cope with the new challenges faced, and to introduce the new EZ Classrooms and Zoom lessons for students. <br><br></div><div>Although a small business, EZ Learn Books seems to have found a niche in the market, and I thank everyone concerned for their loyal support and positive feedback. EZ Learn remains committed to providing materials that are current, fun, and easy to use, as well as additional support in the form additional resources and personal assistance and advice to any teacher or pupil in need.<br><br>Barbara Williamson<br><br></div>	Company	7	2020-09-15 11:46:38.504473	2020-10-08 17:03:42.358076
452	about	<div>Marisa van der Merwe of MiniChess talks about future-relevant education.</div><div>Education, as we knew it, has changed forever.  MiniChess is part of education-innovation for 21st Century-relevance, as it develops smart-thinking skills in children from 4-years and up, through purpose-designed, neuro-based play-innovations - to empower the StartSmart Entrepreneurs of tomorrow, TODAY.</div><div> </div><div>We know that approximately 1,4 billion children, worldwide, have now moved from the classroom to the digital world of education. The 2020 lock-down has brought HUGE challenges in education BUT also opened-up a WORLD of new opportunities!</div><div> </div><div>Parents are confronted with many challenges: How can I take my child forward inside this Education-disruption?  How do we, as parents, move into the new normal?  How do I empower my child with 21st Century-relevant teaching &amp; training? Many of us are perhaps fearful and thinking, whereto from here?  Children are very adaptable to change, but are we?  As a future-minded Organisation, we believe that there are many opportunities inside this disaster, and we hereby invite you to take our hand to create a winning strategy for our children!</div><div> </div><div><strong>There’s an old Chinese proverb that says,</strong><strong><em> ‘you will stand on a hill for a very long time, with your mouth open before a roasted chicken flies into it’.</em></strong><strong>  Are you standing on that education-hill waiting OR are you ready to hatch &amp; grow-up your own chicks?<br><br>Please </strong><a href="http://homeschoolexpo.africa/events/1/exhibitors/51"><strong>click here</strong></a><strong> to visit our stand.</strong></div><div> </div><div>Contact MiniChess (<a href="mailto:info@minichess.co.za">info@minichess.co.za</a>) to enter your child in the StartSmart Entrepreneurs Club OR if you need more info about MiniChess (including franchise business-opportunities).</div>	Presentation	24	2020-10-07 11