361	introduction	<div>Many families often start their homeschooling journey in confusion, a rare few start with a planned path and method in mind. Whether that method includes Charlotte Mason, living books, delight-directed, project-based learning, or an eclectic method pulled from a diverse set of styles or curriculum, you will certainly wonder how to continue this until Gr.12. Following an eclectic education until Gr.12 can be such a daunting idea. How do you know you are covering everything? How do you choose a program or curriculum? Do you have to teach it all yourself? Will your child be able to study further? Many families aren't aware of the American High School Diploma to receive a formal high school qualification, which is accepted internationally, and in South Africa. <br><br>We are happy to introduce you to <strong>Diversio Learning Academy (DLA)</strong>. We are working in partnership with HomeLife Academy, a USA-based private school that provides academic support and assistance to homeschooling families worldwide. For families with teenagers in high school, <strong>DLA</strong> makes it possible to receive the American High School Diploma as a school leaving certificate. This diploma is approved by USAF to fulfill the requirements needed for acceptance at SA Universities with the completion of either the SAT/ACT. <br>Read our latest newsletter and get to know more about the requirements for the completion of the American high school diploma.<action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSI-Z2lkOi8vZXZlbnRzLXBsYXRmb3JtL0FjdGl2ZVN0b3JhZ2U6OkJsb2IvMTI0Nj9leHBpcmVzX2luBjsAVEkiDHB1cnBvc2UGOwBUSSIPYXR0YWNoYWJsZQY7AFRJIg9leHBpcmVzX2F0BjsAVDA=--32667e068138129c7262ac34f1a9005d0c804937" content-type="application/pdf" url="http://homeschoolexpo.africa/files/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBdDRFIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--2f01590f031a5ec83259ea30a77c7161eea94d8d/Vol%203_The%20Learning%20Journey%20at%20Home%20Newsletter%20(1).pdf" filenam