522	about_exhibitor	<h1><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSI-Z2lkOi8vZXZlbnRzLXBsYXRmb3JtL0FjdGl2ZVN0b3JhZ2U6OkJsb2IvMzMyOT9leHBpcmVzX2luBjsAVEkiDHB1cnBvc2UGOwBUSSIPYXR0YWNoYWJsZQY7AFRJIg9leHBpcmVzX2F0BjsAVDA=--b7730227555f80c0985307180d4dc3488ad8c635" content-type="image/jpeg" url="http://homeschoolexpo.africa/files/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBZ0VOIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--e75f4f39d1e1f97f0d641f5bd67d6fc894b2a1b4/Cambridge.jpg" filename="Cambridge.jpg" filesize="134983" width="761" height="500" previewable="true" presentation="gallery"></action-text-attachment><em>“It takes a village to raise a child.” - African proverb</em></h1><h1> </h1><h1>Global Village College is a Student Centre in Centurion.  We offer a complete online learning solution to prepare your child to acquire the Cambridge International qualifications.  <br>Visit us at 14 Baltimore Road, Pierre van Ryneveld, Centurion.<br><br></h1><h1><strong>WHO WE ARE<br></strong>We are passionate educators who have home schooled our own children.  With extensive expertise and experience in education, consulting and commerce, we guide students on their academic pathway to achieve success in work and life. <br><br></h1><h1>Our Director is a mom who started home schooling her own children in order to provide them with an education she believed would stretch and challenge them to reach their potential and would prepare them for the future.  Her combined expertise in organisation development consultancy and education perfectly equips her to guide students on their academic pathway to find meaningful employment and to learn the skills they need for the 4th Industrial workplace.  She draws on extensive research and diverse experience in youth development, education, school management and finance to help young people on the exciting journey to acquire the skills and qualifications they will need to thrive in a rapidly changing and competitive global world. Tracey holds a Masters degree in Organisation Development and Consulting from Sheffield Hallam University and a Higher Diploma in Education and a Bachelor of Commerce from Stellenbosch University.  Her continuing professional development includes Philosophy for Children (P4C), All Brains Don’t Think Alike and The Education of Highly Able Learners.<br><br></h1><h1>Our Head of Educational Studies is also a mom who has walked the path of home-schooling her son who has dyslexia. As a qualified teacher with an Honours degree in Education, she found that the traditional school system was unable to successfully accommodate her own child's education.  Based on her experience and after exploring all the options available to South African students, she chose Cambridge as her curriculum of choice.  The methodical delivery of curricula, the incredible resources available and the flexibility of the examination series ensure that your child is given the best opportunities and to achieve an internationally recognized matric qualification right here in South Africa. Her experience over the last 16 years as Head of Department, Deputy Principal and Principal has contributed greatly to the knowledge and guidance she can offer our students.<br><br></h1><h1><strong>OUR ACADEMIC TEAM</strong></h1><h1>Our Head of Educational Studies and our subject specialist tutors are qualified and experienced teachers in the Cambridge International system who are passionate about supporting your child in obtaining a Cambridge International qualification.<br><br></h1><h1>In addition to our teaching experience, we bring our diverse local and international life experience to Global Village College. We think you will enjoy meeting our team members who have worked as examiners in the British educational system, local and international heads of school and researchers.  We have on our staff a wildlife management specialist, a designer of optical trapping systems, a researcher in laser beam shaping and a control systems engineer.  One of our staff members was a volunteer on a youth expedition in Chile and another was a tour operator in Malawi!<br><br></h1><h1><strong>OUR VISION <br></strong>Educating for a better world<br><br></h1><h1><strong>OUR GOALS AND VALUE PROPOSITION</strong></h1><h1>We provide a rigorous, adaptive and personalised learning solution which will engage students and prepare them to obtain an internationally recognised qualification.  <br><br></h1><h1>Our courses are competitively priced and we offer a range of options </h1><h1>to suit your child and your family’s situation and needs.<br><br></h1><h1><strong>OUR VALUES<br></strong><br></h1><h1><strong>Personal<br></strong>We recognise every student as an individual.<br>We customise for your child’s needs, interests &amp; passions.<br>We nurture their unique potential &amp; develop their independence.<br>Our approach stretches challenges &amp; inspires.<br>We offer a range of subjects.<br><strong> <br>Future-oriented<br></strong><strong><em>We encourage learners to be: </em></strong><strong><br></strong>Confident<br>Responsible<br>Empowered<br>Innovative<br>Compassionate <br><strong><em>We incorporate 21st Century skills:</em></strong><em> </em><br>Problem solving<br>Creativity<br>Communication<br>Collaboration<br>Digital literacy<br><strong><em>We utilise latest technology.</em></strong><strong><br></strong><br></h1><h1><strong>Global</strong></h1><h1>We develop students with a global mind-set.</h1><h1>We are educational &amp; organisational experts, who collaborate globally. </h1><h1>We constantly research &amp; engage in ongoing professional development.<br><br></h1><h1><strong>Quality Standards<br></strong>We provide rigorous, relevant academic content.<br>The Cambridge International programmes &amp; qualifications </h1><h1>meet the global standard for international education.<br>Our tutors are subject experts.<br><br></h1><h1><strong> <br></strong><br></h1><h1> <br><br></h1><h1> <br><br></h1><div><br></div>	Company	71	2020-10-08 10:35:29.600006	2020-10-15 06:38:44.857907
