182	about_exhibitor	<div>Akademia is in 2011 begin om ŉ Afrikaanse gemeenskapsuniversiteit te wees wat toegang tot universiteitswese in Afrikaans bevorder en dit uitbou in die moderne internasionale samelewing. Akademia onderskei haarself van ander onderriginstansies deur leergeleenthede en studente-ondersteuning deur middel van ’n moderne tegnologiese stelsel aan te bied.<br><br></div><div>Akademia streef daarna om beide hoogstaande opleiding sowel as diepgaande opvoeding te bied. Akademia is ’n Christelike hoëronderwysinstelling wat op ’n oop, onbevange en kritiese wyse ’n leidinggewende rol binne die hedendaagse universiteitswese speel. <br><br></div><div>Akademia is ingevolge die Wet op Hoër Onderwys 101 van 1997 by die Departement van Hoër Onderwys en Opleiding as ŉ privaat Afrikaanse hoëronderwysinstelling geregistreer. Akademia se kwalifikasies is ook deur die Raad op Hoër Onderwys geakkrediteer – dieselfde statutêre liggaam wat openbare universiteite se kwalifikasies in Suid-Afrika akkrediteer.<br><br>In ŉ poging om toeganklike hoër onderwys in Afrikaans te bevorder, bied Akademia nauurse en voltydse studies aan. Voltydse studies word aangebied in Centurion en is ideaal vir skoolverlaters wat voltyds wil studeer en ŉ aktiewe studentelewe wil geniet. Die nauurse onderrigmodel word aangebied oor ŉ landwye netwerk van studiesentrums in Suid-Afrika, en in Namibië. Die nauurse onderrigmodel is ideaal vir studente wat wil werk en nauurs studeer. Gevorderde tegnologie verbind dosente en studente in ŉ virtuele leerruimte </div>	Company	19	2020-09-15 11:51:17.693065	2020-10-07 12:50:39.826825
399	products_and_services	<div>Membership to the CHE  is free.</div><div><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSI-Z2lkOi8vZXZlbnRzLXBsYXRmb3JtL0FjdGl2ZVN0b3JhZ2U6OkJsb2IvMTUyNT9leHBpcmVzX2luBjsAVEkiDHB1cnBvc2UGOwBUSSIPYXR0YWNoYWJsZQY7AFRJIg9leHBpcmVzX2F0BjsAVDA=--22f1d8e621fd0cddf2bff39725c50b5c113551c9" content-type="image/jpeg" url="http://www.homeschoolexpo.africa/files/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBdlVGIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--40644b8ed78d12f12e44dae51e2c9b0ff77c71ef/Image-1%20(2).jpg" filename="Image-1 (2).jpg" filesize="30504" width="629" height="148" previewable="true" presentation="gallery" caption="MySchool Cape Home Educators"></action-text-attachment></div><h1><strong>WHY JOIN THE CHE? </strong></h1><div><br></div><ul><li>To meet, learn from, encourage, and interact with others from all walks of life who have at least one common interest, the desire to home educate our children. We all know that home education takes dedication, commitment, and much more. Interaction with others has many benefits. We can meet other home educators (who may live around the corner) by joining a common organization.</li><li>To stand as a group for events/outing (social and educational). The CHE also organizes a few events per year like the CHE Educational Expo, where curriculum providers and other educational orientated providers display their products, as well as an annual athletics event together with SACCSA.</li><li>By Joining the CHE, we can keep you up to date with what is happening in the Department of Education and our negotiations with them. Whether each individual family decides to register or not, is a personal decision and not the business of CHE. Unfortunately, due to the history of home education in this country, many have been reticent to make themselves known as home educators. It is to your advantage not to be isolated should you need support in a time of uncertainty. Your membership with CHE will be kept confidential.</li><li>There are huge advantages to joining or starting support groups in your area. Taking full responsibility for educating your children can be very stressful, so meeting with people who are going through the same joys or trials is very helpful. Lessons can be shared and group activities organized. If there is a support group already established, we can put you in touch with them, or if there is not, we can help you in starting one.</li><li>We need your on-going involvement and support to enable us to serve you. We have all taken a conscious decision in favor of homeschooling our children; let’s take a conscious step to build home education in South Africa. If we promote home education, there are probably many others who would join us if they knew the benefits and in the long run, we all benefit from the strength of the home education community.</li><li>We need to stand united as a body of people to show that we are organized and that we cannot be ignored. No individual will ever be required by the association to make themselves known. All our data is held in confidence. We cannot act in your interests. Note that there are no paid employees or office bearers. Your contributions of time and money benefit all home educators directly. Office bearers are volunteers and are elected at the AGM annually.</li><li>The organization does not exist to satisfy itself! It must serve its members and it is up to the members to be sure that it does.</li></ul><div><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSI-Z2lkOi8vZXZlbnRzLXBsYXRmb3JtL0FjdGl2ZVN0b3JhZ2U6OkJsb2IvMTUyND9leHBpcmVzX2luBjsAVEkiDHB1cnBvc2UGOwBUSSIPYXR0YWNoYWJsZQY7AFRJIg9leHBpcmVzX2F0BjsAVDA=--6f5ea2537cf90195a7d85f220e918777bf243449" content-type="image/jpeg" url="http://www.homeschoolexpo.africa/files/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBdlFGIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--5f4e4042cb3e02a322b20e4339dc34d9cf9e3368/Image-1%20(1).jpg" filename="Image-1 (1).jpg" filesize="69734" width="676" height="338" previewable="true" presentation="gallery" caption="MySchool Cape Home Educators"></action-text-attachment></div><h1><strong>SUPPORT GROUPS and RESOURCES</strong></h1><div><br>Here is a list of some great Facebook and other groups that are very helpful in finding friends/resources near you:<br><br></div><div>https://www.facebook.com/groups/EducateAtHomeSA/ – S.A Educate At Home Group<br><br></div><div><a href="https://www.facebook.com/groups/homeschoolwesterncape/">https://www.facebook.com/groups/homeschoolwesterncape/</a> – Homeschool Western Cape<br><br></div><div><a href="https://www.facebook.com/groups/656644477732163/">https://www.facebook.com/groups/656644477732163/</a> – Tuisonderrig in Afrikaans<br><br></div><div><a href="http://groups.yahoo.com/group/tuisonderwys">http://groups.yahoo.com/group/tuisonderwys</a> – Homeschool yahoo group (for those not on Facebook <br><br></div><div><a href="https://www.facebook.com/groups/311360395655385/">https://www.facebook.com/groups/311360395655385/</a> – Homeschool exchange (2nd hand material)<br><br></div><div><a href="https://www.facebook.com/groups/559291750891273/">https://www.facebook.com/groups/559291750891273/</a> – Tuisskool koop en verkoop (Afrikaanse hulpbronne: nuut en tweedehands)<br><br></div><div><a href="http://www.tuisskolers.org/">http://www.tuisskolers.org/</a> – Fantastic website with all your homeschool questions answered.<br><br></div><div><a href="http://pestalozzi.org/">http://pestalozzi.org/ </a>– Pestalozzi Trust the legal defense fund for home education<br><br></div><div><a href="http://www.dynamislearning.co.za/">http://www.dynamislearning.co.za/</a> – Dynamis offers seminars and personal consultations with families to determine what approach and curricula will work best for your child and your family.<br><br></div><div><a href="https://www.capehomeed.co.za/general-info/yadafamilies@gmail.com">Yada families</a> – Francois &amp; Suzanne Hattingh focuses on Empowering families: Their hearts are to bring families together and especially draw in NEW home educating families who need support, love, and care!<br><br></div><div>Shirley Erwee has written two fantastic books on homeschooling in SA and has great wisdom and personal experience to offer. Her books are <a href="http://www.south-african-homeschool-curriculum.com/homeschooling-the-primary-years.html"><em>Homeschooling the primary years</em></a> and <a href="http://www.south-african-homeschool-curriculum.com/homeschooling-high-school.html"><em>Homeschooling  High School.<br></em></a><br></div><div><br></div><div>COTTAGE SCHOOLS/LEARNING CENTRES<br>We realize that everyone can not homeschool. Homeschooling is defined when a child receives an education in his/her own home from a parent. Tutors sometimes come in to help, but it all happens in the child’s own home.<br><br></div><div>If you are looking to connect to a cottage school/ small learning center you can use this Facebook group:<br><br></div><div>https://www.facebook.com/groups/WesternCapeLearningCentresAndTutors/<br><br></div><div>We give this information for those who are not able to homeschool their children but advise you to contact the Pestalozzi Trust as this is not legally defined as homeschooling and the Education Department is not kind towards this. The <a href="http://pestalozzi.org/">Pestalozzi Trust</a> can be contacted on  <a href="tel:012%203301337">012 3301337</a>.<br><br></div><div>For more information see:  <a href="https://www.capehomeed.co.za/general-info/_wp_link_placeholder">http://www.tuisskolers.org/centres/learning-centre-information.html<br></a><br></div><div>SACSSA ATHLETICS<br>We have a CHE athletics team that takes part in the <a href="http://sacssa.co.za/">SACSSA</a> Regional, Provincial, and National athletic meet. The Regional meeting usually takes place in February, followed by the Provincial meeting (for those that qualify) shortly after and the National meet around September in Sasolburg.<br><br></div><div>You can join the Athletics telegram channel to receive sports-related information: <a href="https://free.facebook.com/l.php?u=https%3A%2F%2Ft.me%2Fjoinchat%2FAAAAAFJRxGezkwSCkP-4OA%3Ffbclid%3DIwAR0sGrOHmg_Kxuz0F8zfEOgPGdgqM1YFromEcICouvtpqfaS7xPGzFjpu0A&amp;h=AT2YCH-UYcZGaQSIM2FjGlDeNeX6gicsxY3DfxumZeL2Izn2YiNVXEBNwqvT-bWus7B8BT2DTGVh4BMChllVE8WGCDTjXHfqualy4IHaRa6Bd7bpQzKmcc08Lz0H9FWgJaw">https://t.me/­joinchat/­AAAAAFJRxGezkwSCkP-4O­A<br></a><br></div><div>EDUCATIONAL EXPO<br>More information available at <a href="https://homeschoolexpo.co.za/">Homeschool Expo.</a> The Expo usually takes place around September/October each year.<br><br></div><div>PERSONAL SUPPORT CONTACT<br>If you would like to talk to someone, please contact Suzanne Hatting on <a href="mailto:suzannehat@gmail.com">suzannehat@gmail.com<br></a><br></div><div>DVD<br>CHE filmed our 2016 homeschool winter workshop. If you would like to order this very informative dvd, please visit <a href="https://www.capehomeed.co.za/product/winterworkshop_dvd/">product page</a>.<br><br></div>	Company	54	2020-10-01 15:42:06.621263	2020-10-06 08:16:12.346571
