357	products_and_services	<h1>Classes and courses</h1><div><br>Edublox reading, maths and learning clinics and centres specialise in educational interventions – either in one of our 41 outlets, or online with live tutors. These include <strong>cognitive training, reading, spelling, comprehension and mathematics</strong>, which are mainly focused towards primary school learners, however, extend to high school and beyond. <br><br>Our offering is explained in <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=s8sTtq3DGY0">this video</a>, where we compare the learning process to that of building a house.<br><br>We offer clients:<br><br></div><ul><li>A scientific assessment of the learner’s reading and learning skills. </li><li>Weekly classes to improve concentration, perception, memory, logical thinking, reading, reading speed, spelling ability, comprehension and mathematics. </li><li>Help for learners with reading and spelling difficulties, including reversals of letters such as ‘b’ and ‘d’. </li><li>Intensive holiday courses and one-on-one sessions for accelerated progress and results. </li><li>Studiblox: Classes on study skills, study methods and study techniques for Grade 4 and older learners. </li><li>English First Additional Language course – a course integrated with cognitive exercises that allow for faster learning and increased memory retention, with the potential to promote performance in other subjects.</li><li>Afrikaans First Additional Language course – a customised course focusing on speaking &amp; writing, vocabulary and phonics as opposed to grammar only. Grade 2 - 6) </li><li>Academic bridging programme: EASY (Edublox Academic Success Year), a specialised and personalised tutoring services for Grade 1 – 7 learners.</li><li>Online solutions to develop foundational cognitive skills through the Edublox Online Tutor ‘Development Tutor’ and ‘Reading Tutor’ programs. </li></ul><div>For more information about Edublox's classes and courses, click <a href="https://www.edubloxsa.co.za/classes-and-courses/">here</a>.<br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSI-Z2lkOi8vZXZlbnRzLXBsYXRmb3JtL0FjdGl2ZVN0b3JhZ2U6OkJsb2IvMjMwMj9leHBpcmVzX2luBjsAVEkiDHB1cnBvc2UGOwBUSSIPYXR0YWNoYWJsZQY7AFRJIg9leHBpcmVzX2F0BjsAVDA=--fc5d6c7095829349f7a268637fed9d648cf0f6c8" content-type="image/png" url="http://homeschoolexpo.africa/files/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBdjRJIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--93ed7c4d25ca9745d082ac0d05de576e964c1391/Updated%20Flyers%202020%20Online%20Services.png" filename="Updated Flyers 2020 Online Services.png" filesize="3535832" width="1408" height="2000" previewable="true" presentation="gallery"></action-text-attachment></div>	Company	49	2020-09-29 11:51:25.253001	2020-10-12 14:31:28.102856
445	products_and_services	<blockquote> <br>Do any of your kids have the “writing gene”? Or do you have <strong>writing-phobic children</strong> who pretty much resist anything having to do with pencil and paper?<br><br>No matter what kind of learner you have, teaching writing can be intimidating or overwhelming. Even if you’re a writer, it doesn’t automatically mean you know how to teach writing. Putting words on paper might come naturally to you, but how do you pass on what you know and love to a child who hates it?<br><br><action-text-attachment content-type="image" url="https://writeshop.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/WriteShop-All-Covers-web.png" width="900" height="900"></action-text-attachment><br><a href="https://writeshop.com/our-story/">We’ve been there</a>. <strong>We understand the challenges of teaching writing</strong>. That’s why we’ve created materials that teach your child how to write—<em>and</em> show you how to teach. Whether your children are very young or well into their teens, WriteShop’s step-by-step lessons will help you introduce and review the building blocks of the writing process.<br><br><h1><strong>Writing Curriculum for All Ages</strong></h1><br>WriteShop is an award-winning writing curriculum that has been equipping homeschooling families since 2001. We have <strong>resources for all ages</strong>, from kindergarten through high school.<br><br><h1>Placement Quiz</h1></blockquote><div><action-text-attachment content-type="image" url="https://writeshop.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/placement-quiz-banner.png" width="1200" height="422"></action-text-attachment></div><h1>WriteShop Primary</h1><div><br>WriteShop Primary is all about helping your child feel successful. Picture books, games, and crafts make writing fun. If your child isn’t reading or writing, that’s OK. Every activity can be done orally.  <a href="https://writeshop.com/writeshop-primary-overview/"><em>Learn more</em></a>…<br><br></div><h1>WriteShop Junior</h1><div><br>This upper-elementary curriculum introduces children to the excitement of writing in different genres, including mysteries, science fiction stories, and nonfiction reports. It’s still important to have fun while learning, so WriteShop Junior activities keep kids engaged with fun games that teach skills but don’t require any writing. Even the editing process is fun!  <a href="https://writeshop.com/writeshop-junior-overview/"><em>Learn more</em></a><em>…<br></em><br></div><h1>WriteShop I and II</h1><div><br>Older students in junior high and high school will tackle descriptive, expository, narrative, and persuasive compositions and essays. They’ll learn to use sentence variations, make strong word choices, and improve their self-editing and proofreading skills.  <a href="https://writeshop.com/writeshop-i-ii-overview/"><em>Learn more</em></a><em>…<br></em><br> <br><br></div>	Company	59	2020-10-07 10:31:48.208185	2020-10-08 17:27:38.48616
