350	introduction	<div><br></div><blockquote><em>We had child welfare on our door because neighbors couldn't mind their own business as to why our kids are home. A legal representative from Pestalozzi Trust took care of everything. You guys are great! - Judy Heyns</em></blockquote><div><br>We protect the rights and freedoms of families and schools to educate children according to their own religious and philosophical persuasions, educational preferences, and cultural traditions. We do this by:<br><br></div><ul><li>Providing advice on the legalities and practicalities of home education</li><li>Resolving any conflict our members may experience with the authorities with regards to their home education</li><li>Engaging with law- and policymakers to create a better legal environment for all South African home educators and small schools</li><li>Encouraging acceptance of home education and small school education by the public by spreading positive and accurate information about home and small school education in the media</li><li>Supporting reliable research with regards to home education</li><li>Using a well-trained, experienced legal team to handle legal actions</li></ul><div> </div><div><strong>Why should my family become a member of the Pestalozzi Trust?</strong></div><div><br></div><blockquote><em>It came as a shock, a Gauteng Education Department official was on the line asking about our home education. A "concerned" family member has contacted the Department. Fortunately, we were members of the Trust. We called the 24/7 helpline and got excellent advice. We sent a single email to the GDE official and never heard from them again. Thank you, Pestalozzi. - MP, Gauteng</em></blockquote><div><br>If your family is a member of the Trust, you will receive a 24/7 emergency number to call when you experience any conflict with the authorities with regards to your home education. This includes conflict with the education department, social workers, schools, the police, etc.</div><div> </div><div>The Trust will assist you in resolving this conflict in a manner that is in your family’s best interest. Should assistance from a legal professional be required, the Trust will source and brief experienced professionals and cover all costs involved in legal proceedings.</div><div> </div><div>You will also be kept up to date with the most recent and accurate information with regards to the legalities of home education.</div><div> </div><div><strong>Why should my small school (cottage school, learning center, etc.) become a member of the Trust?</strong></div><div> </div><div>If your school is a member of the Trust, you will receive a 24/7 emergency number to call when you experience any conflict with the authorities with regards to the education provided at your school. (Please note that this does not include conflict with regards to zoning or other municipal problems.) The Trust will assist you in resolving this conflict in a manner that is in your learners’ best interests.</div><div> </div><div>The Trust can also assist you, should you experience difficulty and/or conflict with the registration procedure.</div><div> </div><div>You will also be kept up to date with the most recent and accurate information with regards to the legalities of small school education.</div><div> </div><blockquote><em>As a Cottage School, membership with the Pestalozzi Trust [and] having personally met with the Deputy of the Western Cape Education Department, the advise, support, service [and] guidance from the Pestalozzi Trust was truly professional, kind, informative, had clear boundaries [and] legal experience with handling these circumstances effectively. We felt safe, supported and in good hands throughout the whole experience. I have great respect for their authority, expertise, experience [and] professionalism. You do however, need to listen to and heed to thier advice as they have the backing of a strong legal team with very clear legal information [and] legal boundaries to keep you safe [and] protected in educating your child in their best interests. - Tonia Koegelenberg</em></blockquote><div><br>You can read more about the Pestalozzi Trust <a href="https://pestalozzi.org/en/about-us-2/">here</a>.</div><div>U kan <a href="https://pestalozzi.org/wie-is-ons/">hier</a> meer lees oor die Pestalozzi Trust.</div><div>Or contact us at 012 330 1337 or defensor@pestalozzi.org.</div>	Company	48	2020-09-29 10:10:48.432716	2020-10-14 07:13:33.725001
