384	workshop_facilitator_info	<div>Business simulation afford participants the opportunity to create and manage their own business by means of gamification. The simulation aims to boost engagement and motivation to study through teamwork and decision-making skills relying on participants to solve problems. Parents become more than just educators by mentoring rather than teaching. <br> <br>In a world where teenagers are expected and taught to color inside the lines, thinking within the box is often the very thing that keeps the youth contained inside it. Rejecting this notion, Eryquin started coloring outside the lines. She founded a non-profit company and hopes to inspires fellow young adults to reject the <em>status quo</em> of being average. Inspiring teenagers and young adults like herself, to dust their own business plans and build enterprises that will do them and their investors proud.<br> <br>Eryquin, the founder of the MOR Foundation, epitomizes the phrase ‘dynamite comes in small packages. <br> </div><h1>Eryquin is …</h1><div><br></div><div>1. High schooler who gets results…</div><h1><ul><li>Recipient: Open Centenary Scholarship. (2015)</li><li>Academic excellence: (2014; 2015; 2017; 2018; 2019)</li><li>Certificate of distinction (2014; 2016; 2019)</li><li>Academic Full Colors: (2017; 2018; 2019)</li></ul></h1><div><br>2. An accomplished artist …</div><h1><ul><li>Special achievement award: (2017)</li><li>Music: Full colors :(2018; 2019)</li><li>Ballet: Represented South Africa in Miami and Kazakhstan(2016; 2017)</li><li>Double Bass: Tshwane Youth Symphony Orchestra(2016; 2017; 2018)<ul><li>Simfonia Juventi(2017; 2018; 2019)</li><li>University of Pretoria Strings Orchestra(2017; 2018)</li></ul></li></ul></h1><div><br>3. Sporty too…</div><h1><ul><li>SANESA Level 1: working riding, Performance and Dressage (2014)</li><li>Hockey: A Team (2012 – 2017)</li><li>Skydiving</li></ul></h1><div> <br>4. Pretty darn smart…</div><ul><li>But does not pretend to know it all. With the backing of her parents, Fergus and Marina Ferguson, both business and executive coaches and members of the Board of the Mor Foundation, team Ferguson is skilled at breaking down complex issues into simple steps and has the tools to help young entrepreneurs to succeed. </li></ul><div><br> 5. A devoted community member…</div><h1><ul><li>The Mor Foundation (2018)<ul><li>Eryquin is the founder and patron of the Mor-Foundation, a non-profit Company focusing on empowering the youth through entrepreneurial and leadership development programs. </li></ul></li><li>Dare to Lead – Brené Brown – Certification ( 2019)<ul><li>Mentoring the four measurable observable and teachable skillsets of courage, by understanding courage and the role that self-awareness, empathy, values and vulnerability plays in leadership.</li></ul></li></ul></h1><div><br>Living a dual-life of a typical high-schooler, Eryquin aims to change the world, one dream at a time.<br><br>Contact us at: info.morfoundation@gmail.com<br><br>Website:  <a href="https://bit.ly/2GLL1cu">https://bit.ly/2GLL1cu </a><br> </div>	Workshop	5	2020-09-30 13:49:01.752775	2020-10-14 08:06:08.391467
464	introduction	<div><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSI-Z2lkOi8vZXZlbnRzLXBsYXRmb3JtL0FjdGl2ZVN0b3JhZ2U6OkJsb2IvMjUxMz9leHBpcmVzX2luBjsAVEkiDHB1cnBvc2UGOwBUSSIPYXR0YWNoYWJsZQY7AFRJIg9leHBpcmVzX2F0BjsAVDA=--9a862edd26de3effed7e117c5e9d9a78cfb9d4d1" content-type="image/jpeg" url="http://homeschoolexpo.africa/files/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBdEVKIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--b3f16f7d3de1eb92fc3587e55c964a1cf727bb5a/Stall%20banner%202000x500%20Quality.jpg" filename="Stall banner 2000x500 Quality.jpg" filesize="249024" width="2364" height="592" previewable="true" presentation="gallery" caption="Introduction"></action-text-attachment>SA Homeschool Suppliers is a family business that originated with the Erwee family back in 2013 when they found that it was hard to find relevant resources for second language Afrikaans. After trial and error they finally found Afrikaans language workbooks and readers that worked well for them and decided to share these resources with other homeschooling families. Since then the business has grown and new products are being added to help beginner homeschoolers with children in the elementary grades. At primary school level parents really do not need expensive curricula, the books we supply are affordable and help cover the acquisition of the basic skills in Reading, Writing and Arithmetic. <br><br>The George family, who are homeschooling their children in the elementary grades, have taken over the business and are regularly adding products they find to be useful additions to their own eclectic approach where each child's education is being customized according to their unique developmental levels and interests. <br><br><a href="https://sahomeschoolsuppliers.co.za/product-category/our-products/black-friday-specials/">Please visit our website for Black Friday Specials</a><br><br><br><br></div><div><br></div>	Company	62	2020-10-07 13:43:49.215505	2020-11-19 19:24:29.449149
385	workshop_facilitator_info	<div><strong>Nina Hill</strong> has been a homeschool mom for just over 2 years. She has 2 part-time businesses one working with Forever Aloe Vera products and the other an online course aimed at entrepreneurs helping them find their personal business flow. She brings years of coaching experience to the panel too.<br><br><strong>Lyn Maharaj:</strong> " I've been homeschooling my 2 sons for 4 years now. The older one has been to school for 3 years but the younger has just been for a few months. Initially, we took the route of an eclectic approach using my professional degree in Education as a source of splice to plan ahead. We based our work on a more Cambridge route. At this time I created an office in my home so that I would be more available and distribute my time between both schooling and work. </div><div>My Work: I hold a degree in Education and qualification in Commerce and Management. I taught for 15 years. Holding positions in management as well as being involved with Curriculum development and Thinking skills implementation and EQ for children. </div><div>For 10 years now I co-own with my husband,  our family business, and am the Group Financial Director of our manufacturing company.  </div><div>I do public speaking from time to time. And have spoken a lady's meetings often. </div><div>I plan a lot. My teaching background and my views on education especially in our South African schools have led me to make different choices with regards to my children's education. We focus on entrepreneurship and a modern-day Technological advanced approach with skills-based exposure." <br><br><strong>Jeanne Snyman</strong>: "We decided to start homeschooling our 3 kids (four years ago), while both running our own businesses.  I have in this time learned (sometimes the hard way) that although full-on, with good time management and definite boundaries this is very possible.  We've also found that it just becomes part of the homeschool curriculum