386	workshop_facilitator_info	<div><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSI-Z2lkOi8vZXZlbnRzLXBsYXRmb3JtL0FjdGl2ZVN0b3JhZ2U6OkJsb2IvMzI3ND9leHBpcmVzX2luBjsAVEkiDHB1cnBvc2UGOwBUSSIPYXR0YWNoYWJsZQY7AFRJIg9leHBpcmVzX2F0BjsAVDA=--4eec6962ea0f7f812b94d14fb8d551c871607792" content-type="image/jpeg" url="http://homeschoolexpo.africa/files/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBc29NIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--7088cbdd335ef9852f304d40919c0cfdf5fcdccd/nie%20hoogste%20kwaliteit.jpg" filename="nie hoogste kwaliteit.jpg" filesize="110577" width="480" height="640" previewable="true" presentation="gallery" caption="."></action-text-attachment>Martie du Plessis is a qualified remedial therapist, an educational consultant, an home education mentor, and an uncapped Education coach.<br><br>Over the past 31 years,  Martie trained many parents and teachers to aid children with special needs with the last 18 years specializing in help to Home Educating parents. Martie is the founder of the Dynamis Institute and Uncapped Education.</div>	Workshop	3	2020-09-30 13:49:01.769568	2020-10-15 09:58:51.85729
642	presentation_presenter_info	<div>Tracey Howard started homeschooling her own children in order to provide them with an international education which she believed would stretch and challenge them to reach their potential and would prepare them for the future.  <br><br></div><div>Her combined expertise in education and organisation development consultancy equips her perfectly to guide students on their academic pathway to find meaningful employment and to learn the skills they need for the 4th Industrial workplace. She draws on extensive research and diverse experience in youth development, education and school management to help young people on the exciting journey to acquire the skills and qualifications they will need to thrive in a rapidly changing and competitive global world.</div><div> </div><div>Tracey holds a Masters degree in Organization Development and Consulting from Sheffield Hallam University (UK), and a Higher Diploma in Education and a Bachelor of Commerce from Stellenbosch University.  Her continuing professional development includes Philosophy for Children (P4C), All Brains Don’t Think Alike and The Education of Highly Able Learners.</div>	Presentation	40	2020-10-14 10:18:09.224082	2020-10-15 11:11:30.414582
